{"title_page": "Mortadella", "text_new": "{{Use British English|date=February 2014}}\n[[File:Mortadella.jpg|thumb|Mortadella Bologna [[Geographical indications and traditional specialities in the European Union|IGP]] from Italy]]\n[[File:Mortadella tagliata.jpg|thumb|Mortadella Bologna, with [[pistachio]]s, [[Geographical indications and traditional specialities in the European Union|IGP]] from Italy]]\n'''Mortadella''' ({{IPA-it|morta\u02c8d\u025blla}}) is a large [[Italian sausage]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/mortadella|title=Mortadella - Define Mortadella at Dictionary.com|work=Dictionary.com}}</ref> or [[luncheon meat]] (''[[salumi|salume]]'' {{IPA-it|sa\u02c8lu\u02d0me|}}) or according to Ben Keith Kelly a ham, made of finely hashed or ground heat-cured pork, which incorporates at least 15% small cubes of pork fat (principally the hard fat from the neck of the pig). It is traditionally flavoured with [[black pepper]] grains, but modern versions can also contain [[pistachio]]s or, more rarely, [[Myrtle (plant)|myrtle]] berries.\n\nThe best-known version of mortadella is Mortadella Bologna [[Geographical indications and traditional specialities in the European Union|IGP]], but other varieties are found across Italy, including some made of other meats.\n\n==Etymology==\nThe origin of the name ''mortadella'' is debated. One theory derives the name from the [[Latin]] word ''mortarium'' ([[Mortar and pestle|mortar]]), traditionally used to pound the meat to produce the sausage.<ref name=Hazan>{{cite book |last= Hazan|first= Marcella |date= 2012|title= The Essentials of Classic Italian Cooking|url= https://books.google.ch/books?id=IciBQN-0VS4C&pg=PP17|location= |publisher= Pan Macmillan|page= 17|isbn= 9780752228044}}</ref><ref name=Oxford>{{cite book |last= Davidson|first= Alan |date= 2014|title= The Oxford Companion to Food|url= https://books.google.ch/books?id=bIIeBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA533|location= Oxford|publisher= OUP Oxford|page= 533|isbn= 9780191040726}}</ref> This theory, proposed by Giancarlo Susini, professor of ancient history in the [[University of Bologna]], relies on two funerary [[stele]]s kept in the [[Museo Civico Archeologico di Bologna|Archaeological Museum of Bologna]], believed to pertain to the same monument, one showing a herd of piglets and the other a mortar and pestle.<ref name=Roversi1>{{cite book|url= https://mortadellabologna.com/blog/etruschi-galli-bol-o-romani-chi-e-stato-l-inventore/|title= La Mortadella Bologna IGP. Storia di un mito|last= Roversi|first= Giancarlo|date= 2013|location= Bologna|publisher= Consorzio mortadella Bologna|language=IT}}</ref> Another theory, introduced by [[Ovidio Montalbani]] in the [[17th century]], derives the name from a [[Ancient Rome|Roman]] sausage flavoured with [[Myrtus|myrtle]] berries that Romans called ''farcimen myrtatum'' or ''farcimen murtatum'' (myrtle sausage).<ref name=Roversi2>{{cite book|url= https://mortadellabologna.com/blog/mirto-o-mortella-al-posto-del-pepe-troppo-pregato-e-costo/|title= La Mortadella Bologna IGP. Storia di un mito|last= Roversi|first= Giancarlo|date= 2013|location= Bologna|publisher= Consorzio mortadella Bologna|language=IT}}</ref><ref name=Oxford/> <ref name=Hazan/> Myrtle was in fact a popular spice before [[Black pepper|pepper]] became available to European markets.<ref name=Roversi2/>\n\n==History==\nTraditionally, the pork filling was ground to a paste using a large [[Mortar and pestle|mortar]] (''mortaio'' {{IPA-it|mor\u02c8ta\u02d0jo|}}) and pestle. \n\nMortadella originated in [[Bologna]], the capital of [[Emilia-Romagna]]. [[Anna Del Conte]] (''The Gastronomy of Italy'' 2001) found a sausage mentioned in a document of the official body of meat preservers in Bologna dated 1376 that may be mortadella.\n\n==Varieties==\nMortadella Bologna has [[Protected designation of origin|Protected Geographical Indication (IGP)]] status under [[European Union law]], and is the best known world-wide. The zone of production is extensive: as well as [[Emilia-Romagna]] and the neighbouring regions of [[Piedmont]], [[Lombardy]], [[Veneto]], [[Marche]] and Tuscany, it includes Lazio and [[Trentino]].\n\nMortadella di [[Prato]], produced in [[Tuscany]], is also defined by an IGP. It is flavoured with pounded garlic and coloured with [[alchermes]].\n\nThe mortadella of [[Amatrice]], high in the [[Apennine Mountains|Apennines]] of northern [[Lazio]], is lightly smoked.\n\nMortadella di cavallo is made from [[horsemeat]] in [[Albano Laziale]] in [[Lazio]].<ref>[http://www.arsial.it/portalearsial/prd_tipici/scheda_prodotto.asp?tip=0&id=103&bio=0]</ref>\n\nThe American sausage called \"[[Bologna sausage|bologna]]\" is named after the mortadella of Bologna.\n\n==Similar products outside Italy==\n\n===Lusitanic and Hispanic cultures===\n{{unreferenced section|date=June 2017}}\n[[File:Mortadela com azeitonas.jpg|thumb|Mortadella with olives from Portugal]]\nMortadella is very popular in Spain and Portugal, where a variety with [[black pepper|pepper]] and [[olive]]s is widely consumed, especially in sandwiches. In eastern Spain, the standard mortadella is often referred to as ''mortadela italiana'' (Italian mortadella), to differentiate it from a local variant named ''catalana''.\n\nMortadella is also very popular in Argentina, Bolivia, Peru, Brazil, Ecuador, Chile, Colombia, Uruguay and Venezuela, thanks to the Italian immigrants who settled in these countries in the early 20th century. In these countries it is spelled ''mortadela'', and its recipe is quite similar to the traditional Italian, with additional pepper grains.\n\nIn Brazil, [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] has a very popular ''mortadela'' sandwich sold in the Mercado Municipal.\n\nIn Puerto Rico, \"smoked mortadella\" is sometimes confused with commercial salami, or with salami cotto, because cafeterias, panaderias, colmados, and restaurants buy the bulk of whole smoked mortadella. While salami may contain pork, beef, veal and small pieces of fat uniformly distributed within the sausage, mortadella has the traditional larger chunks not so uniformly distributed. Its diameter is much larger than that of hard salami and more closely resembles salami cotto (cooked) in size, hence the confusion of some people. It is smaller in diameter than the traditional mortadella de Bologna because the smoking process causes some shrinkage. It is best served at room temperature to bring out its rich flavour.\n\n===Central, Southern and Eastern Europe===\nIn Romania, a similar cold cut is also known as ''parizer''. It is a type of artisan bologna.\nIn Hungary, a similar product is called, in [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]], ''mortadella'' and a plain variety called ''pariser'', ''parizer'' or ''p\u00e1rizsi''. The term ''parizer'' is also often used in Bosnia-Herzegovina, while ''parizier'' is used in other territories of the Balkans. The classic Italian ''mortadella'' is widely sold in supermarkets along the entire Adriatic coast. \n\nIn Greece, where there is a smaller version in addition to the regular one, that variety is called Parizaki or Mortadelaki, and in Bulgaria, Slovenia, Croatia, Serbia and North Macedonia, the product known as ''mortadela'' is widely eaten. \n\nIn Poland, ''mortadela'' slices are sometimes dipped in batter, fried and served with potatoes and salads as a quicker (and cheaper) alternative to traditional [[pork chop]]s.\n\n===Middle East and North Africa===\nIn several countries, such as Morocco, Algeria, Egypt, Iraq, Syria, Lebanon, Jordan, Palestine, United Arab Emirates, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Kuwait and Israel, [[halal]] or [[kosher]] mortadella is sold, which is made from chicken, beef, or turkey. The Palestinian Siniora brand, established in Jerusalem in 1920<ref>http://www.siniorafood.com/en-us/About-Us/Company-Overview</ref>, is the first in the region, a mortadella with sliced olives, pistachios or pepper.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Farmer Jack \u2014 a Siniora Sons Inc. Company|url = http://farmerjack.ps/en/|website = farmerjack.ps|access-date = 2016-02-11}}</ref> Lebanese Al-Taghziah is a famous brand that is sold around the world.<ref>{{cite web|title=Al-Taghziah|url=http://altaghziah.com/newweb/}}</ref> The most popular brands in the [[Gulf Cooperation Council|GCC]] are [[Americana Group]] and Halwani Brothers.\nIt is also popular in Iran, albeit usually made with beef or lamb, and called commonly ''kaalbas'', from Russian ''kolbasa''.\n\nPork mortadella is sold in Palestine, Egypt, Lebanon, Jordan, Syria, and the UAE.{{citation needed|date=September 2015}}\n\n===United States===\nA similar commercial sausage product that omits the cubes of pork fat, called [[Bologna sausage|bologna]], is popular in the United States. A variety that includes olives and pimentos is called [[olive loaf]].\n\nMortadella is one of the three meats in [[Central Grocery|Central Grocery's]] [[Muffaletta]] Sandwich in [[New Orleans]], [[Louisiana]], [[United States|USA]] along with Holland ham and Genoa salami.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.frenchquarter.com/best-muffulettas-french-quarter-nearby/|title=Best Muffulettas in the French Quarter and Nearby|website=FrenchQuarter.com}}</ref>\n\nMortadella was banned from import into the United States from 1967 to 2000 due to an outbreak of African swine fever in Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2000/02/13/weekinreview/february-6-12-the-return-of-mortadella.html|title=The Return of Mortadella|date=13 February 2000|work=The New York Times}}</ref> This ban was a pivotal part of the plot of the 1971 film [[Lady Liberty (film)|''La mortadella'']] starring [[Sophia Loren]]. The title for the United States release was ''[[Lady Liberty (film)|Lady Liberty]]''.\n\nThe ban in the United States was lifted due to the [[Veterinary equivalency|Veterinary Equivalency Agreement]] that allowed countries to export products that had been shown to be disease-free as part of an overall agreement that would allow products deemed safe in the United States to be exported to the European Union.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2000/02/10/world/bologna-journal-coming-to-a-deli-near-you-a-long-taboo-sausage.html|title=Bologna Journal; Coming to a Deli Near You: A Long-Taboo Sausage|date=10 February 2000|work=The New York Times}}</ref>\n\n===Ukraine and Russia===\nIn Ukraine and Russia, a very similar product is called \"doctor's sausage\" ({{lang-ru|link=no|\u00ab\u0414\u043e\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f\u00bb \u043a\u043e\u043b\u0431\u0430\u0441\u0430}}). However, this product is normally made from a beef and pork mixture, and does not include pieces of fat (sausages with pieces of fat are called \"Lubitelskaya\" and \"Stolichnaya\") or myrtle as a primary spice, being instead flavoured with just [[coriander]] and [[nutmeg]]. It also traditionally contains eggs and milk, which are usually absent in traditional mortadella.\n\n===East Asia===\n''[[Ch\u1ea3 l\u1ee5a]]'' or Vietnamese mortadella is sometimes used as an accompaniment to the Vietnamese dish ''[[b\u00e1nh cu\u1ed1n]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noodlepie.typepad.com/blog/2004/07/stall_1006_banh.html|title=Stall 1006 - Banh Cuon - noodlepie|work=typepad.com}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Mortadella sandwich]]\n*[[Curing (food preservation)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Mortadella}}\n* [http://www.salumi-italiani.it/en/all-about-salumi/mortadella-eng.php Istituto per Valorizzazione dei Salumi]: Mortadella {{in lang|it}}\n* [http://www.prodottitipici.com/prodotto/0506/mortadella-di-bologna.htm Mortadella di Bologna] {{in lang|it}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20050325132243/http://www.pubit.it/sunti/psi0102a.html Carlo Cantoni and Patrizia Cattaneo, \"La mortadella: aspetti attuali tecnici della sua produzione\"] {{in lang|it}}\n* [http://www.cliffordawright.com/history/sausage.html Clifford A. Wright, \"Sausage Peddlers, Vagabonds, and Bandits: Part 1\"]: types of Italian sausage\n\n{{Sausage}}\n\n[[Category:Cuisine of Emilia-Romagna]]\n[[Category:Argentine cuisine]]\n[[Category:Chilean cuisine]]\n[[Category:Cold cut]]\n[[Category:Croatian cuisine]]\n[[Category:Hungarian cuisine]]\n[[Category:Italian products with protected designation of origin]]\n[[Category:Italian sausages]]\n[[Category:Salumi]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use British English|date=February 2014}}\n[[File:Mortadella.jpg|thumb|Mortadella Bologna [[Geographical indications and traditional specialities in the European Union|IGP]] from Italy]]\n[[File:Mortadella tagliata.jpg|thumb|Mortadella Bologna, with [[pistachio]]s, [[Geographical indications and traditional specialities in the European Union|IGP]] from Italy]]\n'''Mortadella''' ({{IPA-it|morta\u02c8d\u025blla}}) is a large [[Italian sausage]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/mortadella|title=Mortadella - Define Mortadella at Dictionary.com|work=Dictionary.com}}</ref> or [[luncheon meat]] (''[[salumi|salume]]'' {{IPA-it|sa\u02c8lu\u02d0me|}}) made of finely hashed or ground heat-cured pork, which incorporates at least 15% small cubes of pork fat (principally the hard fat from the neck of the pig). It is traditionally flavoured with [[black pepper]] grains, but modern versions can also contain [[pistachio]]s or, more rarely, [[Myrtle (plant)|myrtle]] berries.\n\nThe best-known version of mortadella is Mortadella Bologna [[Geographical indications and traditional specialities in the European Union|IGP]], but other varieties are found across Italy, including some made of other meats.\n\n==Etymology==\nThe origin of the name ''mortadella'' is debated. One theory derives the name from the [[Latin]] word ''mortarium'' ([[Mortar and pestle|mortar]]), traditionally used to pound the meat to produce the sausage.<ref name=Hazan>{{cite book |last= Hazan|first= Marcella |date= 2012|title= The Essentials of Classic Italian Cooking|url= https://books.google.ch/books?id=IciBQN-0VS4C&pg=PP17|location= |publisher= Pan Macmillan|page= 17|isbn= 9780752228044}}</ref><ref name=Oxford>{{cite book |last= Davidson|first= Alan |date= 2014|title= The Oxford Companion to Food|url= https://books.google.ch/books?id=bIIeBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA533|location= Oxford|publisher= OUP Oxford|page= 533|isbn= 9780191040726}}</ref> This theory, proposed by Giancarlo Susini, professor of ancient history in the [[University of Bologna]], relies on two funerary [[stele]]s kept in the [[Museo Civico Archeologico di Bologna|Archaeological Museum of Bologna]], believed to pertain to the same monument, one showing a herd of piglets and the other a mortar and pestle.<ref name=Roversi1>{{cite book|url= https://mortadellabologna.com/blog/etruschi-galli-bol-o-romani-chi-e-stato-l-inventore/|title= La Mortadella Bologna IGP. Storia di un mito|last= Roversi|first= Giancarlo|date= 2013|location= Bologna|publisher= Consorzio mortadella Bologna|language=IT}}</ref> Another theory, introduced by [[Ovidio Montalbani]] in the [[17th century]], derives the name from a [[Ancient Rome|Roman]] sausage flavoured with [[Myrtus|myrtle]] berries that Romans called ''farcimen myrtatum'' or ''farcimen murtatum'' (myrtle sausage).<ref name=Roversi2>{{cite book|url= https://mortadellabologna.com/blog/mirto-o-mortella-al-posto-del-pepe-troppo-pregato-e-costo/|title= La Mortadella Bologna IGP. Storia di un mito|last= Roversi|first= Giancarlo|date= 2013|location= Bologna|publisher= Consorzio mortadella Bologna|language=IT}}</ref><ref name=Oxford/> <ref name=Hazan/> Myrtle was in fact a popular spice before [[Black pepper|pepper]] became available to European markets.<ref name=Roversi2/>\n\n==History==\nTraditionally, the pork filling was ground to a paste using a large [[Mortar and pestle|mortar]] (''mortaio'' {{IPA-it|mor\u02c8ta\u02d0jo|}}) and pestle. \n\nMortadella originated in [[Bologna]], the capital of [[Emilia-Romagna]]. [[Anna Del Conte]] (''The Gastronomy of Italy'' 2001) found a sausage mentioned in a document of the official body of meat preservers in Bologna dated 1376 that may be mortadella.\n\n==Varieties==\nMortadella Bologna has [[Protected designation of origin|Protected Geographical Indication (IGP)]] status under [[European Union law]], and is the best known world-wide. The zone of production is extensive: as well as [[Emilia-Romagna]] and the neighbouring regions of [[Piedmont]], [[Lombardy]], [[Veneto]], [[Marche]] and Tuscany, it includes Lazio and [[Trentino]].\n\nMortadella di [[Prato]], produced in [[Tuscany]], is also defined by an IGP. It is flavoured with pounded garlic and coloured with [[alchermes]].\n\nThe mortadella of [[Amatrice]], high in the [[Apennine Mountains|Apennines]] of northern [[Lazio]], is lightly smoked.\n\nMortadella di cavallo is made from [[horsemeat]] in [[Albano Laziale]] in [[Lazio]].<ref>[http://www.arsial.it/portalearsial/prd_tipici/scheda_prodotto.asp?tip=0&id=103&bio=0]</ref>\n\nThe American sausage called \"[[Bologna sausage|bologna]]\" is named after the mortadella of Bologna.\n\n==Similar products outside Italy==\n\n===Lusitanic and Hispanic cultures===\n{{unreferenced section|date=June 2017}}\n[[File:Mortadela com azeitonas.jpg|thumb|Mortadella with olives from Portugal]]\nMortadella is very popular in Spain and Portugal, where a variety with [[black pepper|pepper]] and [[olive]]s is widely consumed, especially in sandwiches. In eastern Spain, the standard mortadella is often referred to as ''mortadela italiana'' (Italian mortadella), to differentiate it from a local variant named ''catalana''.\n\nMortadella is also very popular in Argentina, Bolivia, Peru, Brazil, Ecuador, Chile, Colombia, Uruguay and Venezuela, thanks to the Italian immigrants who settled in these countries in the early 20th century. In these countries it is spelled ''mortadela'', and its recipe is quite similar to the traditional Italian, with additional pepper grains.\n\nIn Brazil, [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] has a very popular ''mortadela'' sandwich sold in the Mercado Municipal.\n\nIn Puerto Rico, \"smoked mortadella\" is sometimes confused with commercial salami, or with salami cotto, because cafeterias, panaderias, colmados, and restaurants buy the bulk of whole smoked mortadella. While salami may contain pork, beef, veal and small pieces of fat uniformly distributed within the sausage, mortadella has the traditional larger chunks not so uniformly distributed. Its diameter is much larger than that of hard salami and more closely resembles salami cotto (cooked) in size, hence the confusion of some people. It is smaller in diameter than the traditional mortadella de Bologna because the smoking process causes some shrinkage. It is best served at room temperature to bring out its rich flavour.\n\n===Central, Southern and Eastern Europe===\nIn Romania, a similar cold cut is also known as ''parizer''. It is a type of artisan bologna.\nIn Hungary, a similar product is called, in [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]], ''mortadella'' and a plain variety called ''pariser'', ''parizer'' or ''p\u00e1rizsi''. The term ''parizer'' is also often used in Bosnia-Herzegovina, while ''parizier'' is used in other territories of the Balkans. The classic Italian ''mortadella'' is widely sold in supermarkets along the entire Adriatic coast. \n\nIn Greece, where there is a smaller version in addition to the regular one, that variety is called Parizaki or Mortadelaki, and in Bulgaria, Slovenia, Croatia, Serbia and North Macedonia, the product known as ''mortadela'' is widely eaten. \n\nIn Poland, ''mortadela'' slices are sometimes dipped in batter, fried and served with potatoes and salads as a quicker (and cheaper) alternative to traditional [[pork chop]]s.\n\n===Middle East and North Africa===\nIn several countries, such as Morocco, Algeria, Egypt, Iraq, Syria, Lebanon, Jordan, Palestine, United Arab Emirates, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Kuwait and Israel, [[halal]] or [[kosher]] mortadella is sold, which is made from chicken, beef, or turkey. The Palestinian Siniora brand, established in Jerusalem in 1920<ref>http://www.siniorafood.com/en-us/About-Us/Company-Overview</ref>, is the first in the region, a mortadella with sliced olives, pistachios or pepper.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Farmer Jack \u2014 a Siniora Sons Inc. Company|url = http://farmerjack.ps/en/|website = farmerjack.ps|access-date = 2016-02-11}}</ref> Lebanese Al-Taghziah is a famous brand that is sold around the world.<ref>{{cite web|title=Al-Taghziah|url=http://altaghziah.com/newweb/}}</ref> The most popular brands in the [[Gulf Cooperation Council|GCC]] are [[Americana Group]] and Halwani Brothers.\nIt is also popular in Iran, albeit usually made with beef or lamb, and called commonly ''kaalbas'', from Russian ''kolbasa''.\n\nPork mortadella is sold in Palestine, Egypt, Lebanon, Jordan, Syria, and the UAE.{{citation needed|date=September 2015}}\n\n===United States===\nA similar commercial sausage product that omits the cubes of pork fat, called [[Bologna sausage|bologna]], is popular in the United States. A variety that includes olives and pimentos is called [[olive loaf]].\n\nMortadella is one of the three meats in [[Central Grocery|Central Grocery's]] [[Muffaletta]] Sandwich in [[New Orleans]], [[Louisiana]], [[United States|USA]] along with Holland ham and Genoa salami.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.frenchquarter.com/best-muffulettas-french-quarter-nearby/|title=Best Muffulettas in the French Quarter and Nearby|website=FrenchQuarter.com}}</ref>\n\nMortadella was banned from import into the United States from 1967 to 2000 due to an outbreak of African swine fever in Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2000/02/13/weekinreview/february-6-12-the-return-of-mortadella.html|title=The Return of Mortadella|date=13 February 2000|work=The New York Times}}</ref> This ban was a pivotal part of the plot of the 1971 film [[Lady Liberty (film)|''La mortadella'']] starring [[Sophia Loren]]. The title for the United States release was ''[[Lady Liberty (film)|Lady Liberty]]''.\n\nThe ban in the United States was lifted due to the [[Veterinary equivalency|Veterinary Equivalency Agreement]] that allowed countries to export products that had been shown to be disease-free as part of an overall agreement that would allow products deemed safe in the United States to be exported to the European Union.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2000/02/10/world/bologna-journal-coming-to-a-deli-near-you-a-long-taboo-sausage.html|title=Bologna Journal; Coming to a Deli Near You: A Long-Taboo Sausage|date=10 February 2000|work=The New York Times}}</ref>\n\n===Ukraine and Russia===\nIn Ukraine and Russia, a very similar product is called \"doctor's sausage\" ({{lang-ru|link=no|\u00ab\u0414\u043e\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f\u00bb \u043a\u043e\u043b\u0431\u0430\u0441\u0430}}). However, this product is normally made from a beef and pork mixture, and does not include pieces of fat (sausages with pieces of fat are called \"Lubitelskaya\" and \"Stolichnaya\") or myrtle as a primary spice, being instead flavoured with just [[coriander]] and [[nutmeg]]. It also traditionally contains eggs and milk, which are usually absent in traditional mortadella.\n\n===East Asia===\n''[[Ch\u1ea3 l\u1ee5a]]'' or Vietnamese mortadella is sometimes used as an accompaniment to the Vietnamese dish ''[[b\u00e1nh cu\u1ed1n]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noodlepie.typepad.com/blog/2004/07/stall_1006_banh.html|title=Stall 1006 - Banh Cuon - noodlepie|work=typepad.com}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Mortadella sandwich]]\n*[[Curing (food preservation)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Mortadella}}\n* [http://www.salumi-italiani.it/en/all-about-salumi/mortadella-eng.php Istituto per Valorizzazione dei Salumi]: Mortadella {{in lang|it}}\n* [http://www.prodottitipici.com/prodotto/0506/mortadella-di-bologna.htm Mortadella di Bologna] {{in lang|it}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20050325132243/http://www.pubit.it/sunti/psi0102a.html Carlo Cantoni and Patrizia Cattaneo, \"La mortadella: aspetti attuali tecnici della sua produzione\"] {{in lang|it}}\n* [http://www.cliffordawright.com/history/sausage.html Clifford A. Wright, \"Sausage Peddlers, Vagabonds, and Bandits: Part 1\"]: types of Italian sausage\n\n{{Sausage}}\n\n[[Category:Cuisine of Emilia-Romagna]]\n[[Category:Argentine cuisine]]\n[[Category:Chilean cuisine]]\n[[Category:Cold cut]]\n[[Category:Croatian cuisine]]\n[[Category:Hungarian cuisine]]\n[[Category:Italian products with protected designation of origin]]\n[[Category:Italian sausages]]\n[[Category:Salumi]]\n", "name_user": "2a02:c7f:bb42:4b00:8c07:45e3:2a67:62df", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Added content)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mortadella"}
{"title_page": "Virgil van Dijk", "text_new": "{{pp-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Dutch association football player}}\n{{EngvarB|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Dutch name|van Dijk|Dijk}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Virgil van Dijk\n| image = 20160604 AUT NED 8876 (cropped).jpg\n| image_size = 235\n| caption = Van Dijk lining up for the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in 2016\n| fullname = Virgil van Dijk<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/84136 |title=Squads for 2016/17 Premier League confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=1 September 2016 |accessdate=11 September 2016}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1991|7|8|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.11v11.com/players/virgil-van-dijk-247921/ |title=Virgil Van Dijk |website=11v11.com |publisher=AFS Enterprises |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Breda]], Netherlands\n| height = 1.93 m<ref>{{cite web |url=https://southamptonfc.com/first-team/virgil-van-dijk |title=Virgil van Dijk |publisher=Southampton F.C. |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170311031725/https://southamptonfc.com/first-team/virgil-van-dijk |archivedate=11 March 2017 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| position = [[Centre-back]]\n| currentclub = [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]\n| clubnumber = 4\n| youthyears1 = 2009\u20132010\n| youthclubs1 = [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]]\n| youthyears2 = 2010\u20132011\n| youthclubs2 = [[FC Groningen|Groningen]]\n| years1 = 2011\u20132013\n| clubs1 = [[FC Groningen|Groningen]]\n| caps1 = 62\n| goals1 = 7\n| years2 = 2013\u20132015\n| clubs2 = [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]\n| caps2 = 76\n| goals2 = 9\n| years3 = 2015\u20132018\n| clubs3 = [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]]\n| caps3 = 67\n| goals3 = 4\n| years4 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs4 = [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]\n| caps4 = 81\n| goals4 = 8<!-- This section is for league goals only.-->\n| nationalyears1 = 2011\n| nationalteam1 = [[Netherlands national under-19 football team|Netherlands U19]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 1\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2011\u20132013\n| nationalteam2 = [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|Netherlands U21]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 3\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2015\u2013\n| nationalteam3 = [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 33\n| nationalgoals3 = 4\n| medaltemplates = {{Medal|Sport|Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{Medal|Country|{{fb|NED}}}}\n{{Medal|Comp|[[UEFA Nations League]]}}\n{{Medal|Silver|[[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals|2019 Portugal]]|}}\n| club-update = 14:24, 7 March 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 08:54, 20 November 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Virgil Van Dijk''' ({{IPA-nl|v\u0251n \u02c8d\u025bik}}; born 8 July 1991) is a Dutch professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for English {{English football updater|Liverpoo}} club [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] and [[captain (association football)|captains]] the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]]. Considered to be one of the best defenders in the world, he is known for his strength, leadership and aerial ability.<ref name=\"Best Defender-sportbible\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.sportbible.com/football/reactions-take-a-bow-news-virgil-van-dijk-voted-the-best-defender-in-world-football-20190316|title=Virgil Van Dijk Voted The Best Defender In World Football|date=16 March 2019|website=www.sportbible.com|access-date=20 April 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"best defender-sky\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11669/11659594/virgil-van-dijk-the-best-defender-in-the-world-says-paul-merson|title=Virgil van Dijk the best defender in the world, says Paul Merson|website=Sky Sports|access-date=20 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2618579.html|title=Virgil van Dijk: Champions League Defender of the Season|last=UEFA.com|website=UEFA.com|language=en|access-date=2019-09-01}}</ref> In 2019 he was named the [[UEFA Men's Player of the Year Award|UEFA Men's Player of the Year]], and finished runner-up for the [[Ballon d'Or]] and [[The Best FIFA Football Awards 2019|The Best FIFA Men's Player]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/the-best-fifa-football-awards/best-fifa-mens-player/|title=The Best FIFA Men's Player|website=www.fifa.com|accessdate=2 September 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"UEFAMPOTY19\">{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2618573.html|title=Virgil van Dijk wins UEFA Men's Player of the Year award|publisher=UEFA|accessdate=29 August 2019|date=29 August 2019}}</ref> He is the only defender to be nominated for the [[Ballon d'Or]].\n\nAfter beginning his professional career with [[FC Groningen|Groningen]], Van Dijk moved to [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] in 2013, where he won the [[Scottish Premiership]] and was named in the [[PFA Scotland Team of the Year]] in both of his seasons with the club, also winning the [[Scottish League Cup]] in the latter. In September 2015, he joined Premier League side [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] before signing for Liverpool in January 2018 for \u00a375&nbsp;million, a [[List of most expensive association football transfers|world record transfer fee]] for a defender at the time.<ref name=BBCLiverpool/> Van Dijk was involved in reaching the [[2018 UEFA Champions League Final]] during his first spring at Liverpool. In his first full season at the club Van Dijk was named the [[PFA Players' Player of the Year|PFA Player of the Year]] and the [[Premier League Player of the Season]] for the 2018\u201319 season.<ref name=\"BBC 280419\"/><ref name=\"PL POTS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/1214766|title=Van Dijk named EA SPORTS Player of the Season|publisher=Premier League|accessdate=12 May 2019|date=12 May 2019}}</ref> Van Dijk starred as Liverpool won the [[2019 UEFA Champions League Final]] where he was named man of the match.<ref name=\"MOTM\"/> The following season he played in the club\u2019s victorious [[2019 FIFA Club World Cup Final]].<ref name=\"FIFA Final\"/>\n\nVan Dijk made his international debut for the Netherlands in 2015 and became captain of his country in 2018. In 2018, he scored his first international goal in a 3\u20130 win over European champions [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]]. He later captained them to the inaugural [[2019 UEFA Nations League Final]] where they finished runners-up.\n\n==Club career==\n===Early life and career===\nVan Dijk was born in [[Breda]] to a [[Dutch people|Dutch]] father and a [[Surinamese people|Surinamese]] mother.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.celticfc.net/newsstory?item=4174 |title=News |publisher=Celtic F.C. |accessdate=16 May 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029210911/http://www.celticfc.net/newsstory?item=4174 |archivedate=29 October 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Growing up he would play football wherever he could \u2013 on the streets, in concrete cages, and eventually Saturday morning matches.<ref>{{cite news |title=Virgil van Dijk exclusive: \u201cI\u2019m not going to lie, I was pretty scared \u2013 I could have died\u201d |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/virgil-van-dijk-exclusive-im-not-going-lie-i-was-pretty-scared-i-could-have-died#TWOCEsmY6Jcvxwi7.99 |accessdate=5 November 2019 |work=Four Four Two}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Virgil van Dijk: Birthplace of Dreams {{!}} Nike|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O8d_VA6eE2M|language=en|access-date=2019-12-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nike.com/il/football/virgil-van-dijk-birthplace-of-dreams|title=Virgil van Dijk|website=Nike.com|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-12-05}}</ref> He combined his time playing at the [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]] academy with a part-time job as a dishwasher.<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/47283936|title=Virgil van Dijk wants to be 'a legend of Liverpool' - in-depth wide-ranging BBC interview|date=21 February 2019|website=BBC Sport}}</ref><ref name=espn>{{cite news|url=http://africa.espn.com/football/club/liverpool/364/blog/post/3824468/virgil-van-dijk-is-the-best-player-in-the-premier-league-how-the-dutch-defender-became-liverpools-leader|title=Virgil van Dijk is the best player in the Premier League: how the Dutch defender became Liverpool's leader|publisher=ESPN|last=Kuper|first=Simon|date=16 April 2019|accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref> Having previously and unsuccessfully featured as a right-back, Van Dijk was shifted into a central defensive position in 2008, aged 17, after he grew in height by around 18 centimetres.<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\"/><ref name=espn/> Despite the positional shift and Van Dijk's physical growth, Willem II's reserve manager at the time [[Edwin Hermans]] believed he had \"too many limitations\" which prevented him from breaking into the first team.<ref name=espn/> In 2010, he was scouted by former Dutch international [[Martin Koeman]], who was working for [[FC Groningen]] at the time, and he ended up completing a free transfer to the club in the same year.<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\"/><ref name=espn/>\n\n===Groningen===\n\nVan Dijk initially struggled to break into Groningen's first team with club staff believing he was \"overtired\" after extensive playing time with Willem II's academy and reserve sides.<ref name=espn/> He made his professional debut for the club on 1 May 2011, coming on as a 72nd-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Petter Andersson]] during a 4\u20132 victory against [[ADO Den Haag]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2011/05/01/netherlands/eredivisie/hfc-ado-den-haag/stichting-fc-groningen/941703/ |title=ADO Den Haag VS. Groningen 2\u20134 |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform group |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On 29 May, and against the same opposition, he made his first start for Groningen and scored his first professional goals, netting twice in a 5\u20131 win in a [[UEFA Europa League]] play-off match.<ref name=espn/>\n\nDuring the [[2011\u201312 Eredivisie]] season, Van Dijk made 23 league appearances for the [[Eredivisie]] team, and scored his first regular-season goal during the club's 6\u20130 victory over [[Feyenoord]] on 30 October 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soccerbox.com/blog/virgil-van-dijk-premier-league/ |title=Virgil van Dijk One of the Finest Centre-Backs in the Premier League |website=Soccer Box}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/152437/eredivisie-fc-groningen-feyenoord/ |title=Wedstrijd: FC Groningen \u2013 Feyenoord |website=FCUpdate.nl}}</ref> He suffered a personal setback during the campaign, however, as soon after his 20th birthday he was admitted to hospital with [[peritonitis]] and kidney poisoning. Van Dijk later revealed that he had been close to dying as a result of the medical emergency and that the hospital had even gone so far as to ask him to sign a \"sort of [[Will and testament|will]]\" in the event of his passing.<ref name=espn/>\n\nHe did, however, return to Groningen and continued to impress the following season. At the end of the campaign, and with Van Dijk having \"outgrown\" the club, he was offered to a number of bigger Eredivisie clubs, including [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], all of whom elected not to sign him.<ref name=espn/> Instead, in June 2013, he joined Scottish side [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]].<ref name=espn/>\n\n===Celtic===\n====2013\u201314 season====\nOn 21 June 2013, Van Dijk signed with [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] for a fee of around \u00a32.6&nbsp;million, on a four-year deal including a 10% selling-on fee for Groningen.<ref>{{cite news |title=Virgil van Dijk: Dutch defender joins Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/23004736 |website=BBC Sport |date=21 June 2013 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> He made his debut on 17 August, replacing [[Efe Ambrose]] for the final 13 minutes of a 2\u20130 [[Scottish Premiership]] win over [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]] at [[Pittodrie Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Keir |last=Murray |title=Aberdeen 0\u20132 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/23644812 |website=BBC Sport |date=17 August 2013 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> A week later, he made his first start, in a 2\u20132 draw with [[Inverness Caledonian Thistle F.C.|Inverness Caledonian Thistle]] at [[Celtic Park]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Celtic 2\u20132 Inverness CT |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/23737036 |website=BBC Sport |date=24 August 2013 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On 9 November, Van Dijk scored his first Celtic goals, heading one in each half of a 4\u20131 win against [[Ross County F.C.|Ross County]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Martin |last=Conaghan |title=Ross County 1\u20134 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/24783003 |website=BBC Sport |date=9 November 2013 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> After a solo run, he scored the only goal of a victory over [[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]] on 26 December.<ref>{{cite news |first=Andy |last=Campbell |title=St Johnstone 0\u20131 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/25442036 |website=BBC Sport |date=26 December 2013 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nVan Dijk scored again on 26 January 2014, in a 4\u20130 win versus [[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]] for Celtic's 11th consecutive league win.<ref>{{cite news |first=Keir |last=Murray |title=Hibernian 0\u20134 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/25798579 |website=BBC Sport |date=26 January 2014 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On 25 February, he was sent off after 13 minutes of an eventual 2\u20131 loss at Aberdeen, for a professional foul on [[Peter Pawlett]]; it was Celtic's first defeat of the season.<ref>{{cite news |first=Andrew |last=Southwick |title=Aberdeen 2\u20131 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/25892139 |website=BBC Sport |date=25 February 2014 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> With Celtic having already won the league, Van Dijk netted again on 7 May to put his team 3\u20131 up away to St Johnstone, in an eventual 3\u20133 draw.<ref>{{cite news |first=Cheri |last=Burns |title=St Johnstone 3\u20133 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/27216459 |website=BBC Sport |date=7 May 2014 |accessdate=17 October 2015}}</ref> He was one of three Celtic players named in the [[PFA Scotland Team of the Year]].<ref name=1314PFA>{{cite news |title=Celtic and Dundee United trios in SPFL Premiership team of year |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/27080030 |website=BBC Sport |date=18 April 2014 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> Van Dijk was nominated for the [[PFA Scotland Players' Player of the Year]] award,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://spfl.co.uk/news/article/pfa-player-of-year-nominees/ | title=PFA Player of the Year nominees | publisher=[[Scottish Professional Football League|SPFL]] | date=16 April 2014 | accessdate=12 May 2019}}</ref> but lost out to fellow Celtic player [[Kris Commons]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://spfl.co.uk/news/article/pfa-scotland-award-winners/ | title=PFA Scotland award winners | publisher=[[Scottish Professional Football League|SPFL]] | date=27 April 2014 | accessdate=12 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n====2014\u201315 season====\n[[File:Virgil van Dijk 2015.jpg|thumb|upright|Van Dijk playing for [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] in 2015]]\n\nOn 22 July 2014, Van Dijk and [[Teemu Pukki]] each scored twice in a 4\u20130 home win over [[Knattspyrnuf\u00e9lag Reykjav\u00edkur|KR]] in a [[UEFA Champions League]] qualifier, putting their team into the next round 5\u20130 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite news |first=Ben |last=Burrows |title=Celtic 4\u20130 KR Reykjavik: Hoops ease into next Champions League round in comfortable fashion |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/celtic-4-0-kr-reykjavik-hoops-3897700 |newspaper=Daily Mirror |location=London |date=22 July 2014 |accessdate=17 October 2015}}</ref> His first goal of the [[2014\u201315 Scottish Premiership|Premiership season]] came on 9 November, finishing from [[Stefan Johansen]]'s last-minute corner for a 2\u20131 win at Aberdeen.<ref>{{cite news |first=Colin |last=Moffat |title=Aberdeen 1\u20132 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/29868766 |website=BBC Sport |date=9 November 2014 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> Three weeks later, Van Dijk scored the first and last goals of Celtic's 4\u20130 win versus [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Heart of Midlothian]] in the fourth round of the [[Scottish Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Andrew |last=Southwick |title=Heart of Midlothian 0\u20134 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/30166217 |website=BBC Sport |date=30 November 2014 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> Four days after that, his sixth goal of the season was enough for victory in a home match against [[Glasgow]] neighbours [[Partick Thistle F.C.|Partick Thistle]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Richard |last=Wilson |title=Celtic 1\u20130 Partick Thistle |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/28647040 |website=BBC Sport |date=4 December 2014 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nVan Dijk was again on target on 21 January 2015, opening a 4\u20130 home win over [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Colin |last=Moffat |title=Celtic 4\u20130 Motherwell |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/30808448 |website=BBC Sport |date=21 January 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On 26 February, he was sent off in the 36th minute against [[Inter Milan]] for a foul on [[Mauro Icardi]], as Celtic lost 1\u20130 on the night, 4\u20133 on aggregate in the last 32 of the [[UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Craig |last=Swan |title=Inter 1 Celtic 0 (4\u20133 agg): Late strike finishes off battling ten-man Celtic and ends their Europa League run |url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-match-reports/inter-1-celtic-0-4-3-5239236 |newspaper=Daily Record |location=Glasgow |date=26 February 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> He was again sent off on 8 March in the Cup quarter-final away to [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] at [[Tannadice Park]], receiving a red card after eleven minutes for a confrontation with [[Calum Butcher]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Keir |last=Murray |title=Dundee United 1\u20131 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31680308 |website=BBC Sport |date=8 March 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> His suspension for the following week's [[2015 Scottish League Cup Final|Scottish League Cup Final]] was overturned on appeal, as was that of [[Paul Paton]], who was sent off when mistaken for Butcher.<ref>{{cite news |title=Van Dijk and Paton cleared to play in League Cup final |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31858622 |website=BBC Sport |date=12 March 2015 |accessdate=18 October 2015}}</ref> Van Dijk played the full 90 minutes of the final at [[Hampden Park]], which Celtic won 2\u20130.<ref name=2015SLC>{{cite news |first=Richard |last=Wilson |title=Dundee United 0\u20132 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31785677 |website=BBC Sport |date=15 March 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On 18 March, Celtic's third consecutive match against Dundee United, Van Dijk scored in the last minute to confirm a 4\u20130 win in a Cup replay.<ref>{{cite news |title=Celtic 4\u20130 Dundee United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31826157 |website=BBC Sport |date=18 March 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 April, Celtic contested the Cup semi-final against Inverness at Hampden, and Van Dijk opened the scoring with a free kick. After the dismissal of goalkeeper [[Craig Gordon]], Celtic fell 3\u20132, ending their chance of a [[Treble (association football)|treble]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Clive |last=Lindsay |title=Inverness Caledonian Thistle 3\u20132 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32089585 |website=BBC Sport |date=19 April 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> Three days later, again from a free kick, he confirmed a 2\u20131 win away to [[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Andrew |last=Southwick |title=Celtic 1\u20132 Dundee |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31827990 |website=BBC Sport |date=22 April 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> His team again won the league, and Van Dijk was included in the league's Team of the Season for the second consecutive campaign.<ref name=1415PFA>{{cite news |first=Gregor |last=Kyle |title=The SPFL dream team: PFA Scotland announce their teams of the year |url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/spfl-dream-team-pfa-scotland-5616035 |newspaper=Daily Record |location=Glasgow |date=1 May 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> He was again shortlisted for the PFA Scotland Players' Player award,<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32435212 | title=Celtic's Van Dijk & Johansen join Rooney & Stewart in award mix | website=BBC Sport | date=23 April 2015 | accessdate=12 May 2019}}</ref> but lost out to another teammate, this time [[Stefan Johansen]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32578058 | title=Stefan Johansen: Celtic midfielder named Scottish PFA player of the year |website=BBC Sport | date=3 May 2015 | accessdate=12 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nVan Dijk was reportedly \"considering his future\" in Glasgow after Celtic were knocked out of the [[2015\u201316 UEFA Champions League]] in the qualifying rounds to [[Malm\u00f6 FF|Malm\u00f6]] of Sweden.<ref>{{cite news |title=Virgil van Dijk: Celtic defender considers future after defeat |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34060123 |website=BBC Sport |date=26 August 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Southampton===\nOn 1 September 2015, Van Dijk signed a five-year contract with [[Premier League]] club [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]], managed by [[Ronald Koeman]], for a reported \u00a313&nbsp;million transfer fee.<ref>{{cite web |title=Saints complete deadline-day deal for van Dijk |url=https://southamptonfc.com/news/2015-09-01/saints-complete-deadline-day-deal-for-van-dijk |publisher=Southampton F.C. |date=1 September 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Virgil van Dijk: Southampton sign Celtic defender for \u00a313m |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34115519 |website=BBC Sport |date=1 September 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==== 2015\u201316 season ====\nHe made his debut for Southampton on 12 September in a 0\u20130 draw against [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] at [[The Hawthorns]].<ref name=\"sb1516\" /> Two weeks later, Van Dijk marked his third Premier League appearance with his first goal for the club, which came in the form of a header in the 11th minute to put Southampton in front, following a set-piece from [[James Ward-Prowse]] in a 3\u20131 home win over [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Saj |last=Chowdhury |title=Southampton 3\u20131 Swansea City |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34299542 |website=BBC Sport |date=26 August 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On 7 May 2016, Van Dijk signed a new six-year contract with the Saints.<ref>{{cite news |title=Virgil van Dijk: Dutch defender signs new six-year deal at Southampton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36236667 |website=BBC Sport |date=7 May 2016 |accessdate=8 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n==== 2016\u201317 season ====\nOn 22 January 2017, he was named team captain of Southampton, after the departure of [[Jos\u00e9 Fonte]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://southamptonfc.com/news/2017-01-22/claude-puel-captains-southampton-virgil-van-dijk-steven-davis |title=Puel confirms Saints' new captains |publisher=Southampton F.C. |date=22 January 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On the same day, he suffered an ankle injury against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Andy |last=Charles |title=Southampton's Virgil van Dijk out for at least two months with ankle injury |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11700/10753362/southamptons-virgil-van-dijk-out-for-at-least-two-months-with-ankle-injury |publisher=Sky Sports |date=2 February 2017 |accessdate=28 December 2017}}</ref> This ruled him out of the [[2017 EFL Cup Final]], which Southampton lost to [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] at [[Wembley Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title=Manchester United 3\u20132 Southampton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39018813 |website=BBC Sport |date=26 February 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nAfter a successful [[2016\u201317 Southampton F.C. season|2016\u201317 season]] at Southampton, Van Dijk was subject to interest from [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], who apologised to Southampton for an illegal approach for the player after having reportedly made clear his interest in a move to Liverpool.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40194862 |title=Virgil van Dijk: Liverpool apologise & end interest in Southampton defender |website=BBC Sport |date=7 June 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40164572 |title=Virgil van Dijk: Southampton defender keen on Liverpool move |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=5 June 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40170351 |title=Virgin van Dijk: Southampton to report Liverpool over approach |website=BBC Sport |date=6 June 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On 7 August 2017, Van Dijk handed in a transfer request to Southampton and released a statement along with it, emphasising his wish to join a different club in the transfer window.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40855579 |title=Virgil van Dijk: Southampton defender hands in transfer request |website=BBC Sport |date=7 August 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==== 2017\u201318 season ====\nVan Dijk remained with Southampton for the start of the [[2017\u201318 Southampton F.C. season|2017\u201318 season]] and made his first appearance since being injured in January, coming on as a late substitute in a 1\u20130 victory at [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] on 26 September.<ref>{{cite news |first=Luke |last=Reddy |title=Crystal Palace 1\u20130 Southampton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41210053 |website=BBC Sport |date=16 September 2017 |accessdate=25 September 2017}}</ref> He made what turned out to be his final appearance for Southampton on 13 December 2017, in a 4\u20131 home defeat to Leicester.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42247116 |title=Southampton 1\u20134 Leicester City |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=13 December 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> It was also his last appearance in any of Southampton's matchday squads, as he was omitted from the squad for the rest of his tenure at the club in light of speculation surrounding his future.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/transfers/virgil-van-dijk-transfer-news-manchester-city-liverpool-left-out-of-squad-60m-latest-updates-a8128666.html |title=Virgil van Dijk left out of Southampton squad as Mauricio Pellegrino refuses to draw on Manchester City interest |first=Jack |last=De Menezes |newspaper=The Independent |location=London |date=26 December 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Liverpool===\nOn 27 December 2017, it was announced that Van Dijk would join Liverpool when the winter transfer window opened on 1 January 2018<ref name=pressLiverpool>{{cite web |title=Liverpool agree deal to sign Virgil van Dijk |url=http://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/285500-liverpool-agree-deal-to-sign-virgil-van-dijk |publisher=Liverpool F.C. |date=27 December 2017 |accessdate=28 December 2017}}</ref><ref name=southamptonpress>{{cite web |url=https://southamptonfc.com/news/2017-12-27/virgil-van-dijk-southampton-liverpool-transfer-agreement-announcement |title=Van Dijk deal agreed |publisher=Southampton F.C. |date=27 December 2017 |accessdate=28 December 2017}}</ref> for a reported fee of \u00a375&nbsp;million.<ref name=BBCLiverpool>{{cite news |title=Virgil van Dijk: Liverpool to sign Southampton defender for world record \u00a375m |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42496637 |website=BBC Sport |date=27 December 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> Former club Celtic would receive 10% of Van Dijk's transfer fee, due to a sell-on clause placed in his Southampton contract.<ref name=BBCLiverpool/><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11787/10906958/virgil-van-dijk-transfer-would-land-celtic-bumper-windfall |title=Virgil van Dijk transfer would land Celtic bumper windfall |first=Peter |last=Gilbert |publisher=Sky Sports |date=8 June 2017 |accessdate=28 December 2017}}</ref> Southampton claimed the undisclosed transfer fee would constitute a world record fee in football for a defender.<ref name=southamptonpress/>\n\n==== 2017\u201318 season ====\nHe made his debut for Liverpool on 5 January in the third round of the [[FA Cup]] and scored the winning goal with a late header in a 2\u20131 victory against local rivals [[Everton F.C.|Everton]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title=Liverpool 2\u20131 Everton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42508636 |website=BBC Sport |date=5 January 2018 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> In doing so, he became the first player since [[Bill White (footballer, born 1877)|Bill White]] in 1901 to score on his debut in the [[Merseyside derby]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/how-virgil-van-dijk-keeps-14120970 |title=How Virgil van Dijk keeps on creating Liverpool history \u2013 and the remarkable numbers behind derby triumph |work=Liverpool Echo |last=Doyle |first=Ian |date=6 January 2018 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> Van Dijk and [[Dejan Lovren]] built a strong partnership at the heart of Liverpool's defence, with the Dutchman being credited for improving Liverpool's previous defensive issues.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-champions-final-vandijk/van-dijk-has-made-me-a-better-player-says-liverpools-lovren-idUKKCN1IN301 |title=Van Dijk has made me a better player, says Liverpool's Lovren |last=Robinson |first=Neil |agency=Reuters |date=22 May 2018 |accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/apr/09/virgil-van-dijk-brings-calm-and-confidence-to-liverpool |title=Virgil van Dijk brings calm and collective spirit to Liverpool's defence |last=Hunter |first=Andy |date=9 April 2018 |work=The Guardian |accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/how-virgil-van-dijk-redefined-12213864 |title=How dominant Virgil van Dijk has redefined Liverpool's defence |last=Maddock |first=David |date=19 March 2018 |work=Daily Mirror |accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nVan Dijk was included in the [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League#Squad of the Season|UEFA Champions League Squad of the Season]], despite playing just half of the season in the [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]], with the ''UEFA Technical Observers'' saying: \"Van Dijk arrived at [[Anfield]] and provided composure and stability in the [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|competition's knockout stages]].\" Van Dijk played the full 90 minutes in the [[2018 UEFA Champions League Final]] against [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]], which Liverpool lost 1\u20133.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2018/matches/round=2000885/match=2021711/index.html |title=UEFA Champions League \u2013 Real Madrid-Liverpool |publisher=UEFA |accessdate=6 July 2018}}</ref> Van Dijk played 22 games in all competitions in his first season with the club, scoring 1 goal.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://us.soccerway.com/players/virgil-van-dijk/188624/ |title=Netherlands \u2013 V. van Dijk \u2013 Profile |website=soccerway |accessdate=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==== 2018\u201319 season ====\nOn 20 August 2018, Van Dijk was voted [[Player of the match|Man of the Match]] by [[BBC Sport]] and [[Sky Sports]] for his performance in a 2\u20130 win over [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45165666 |title=Crystal Palace 0\u20132 Liverpool: James Milner and Sadio Mane score as Reds move to six points |date=20 August 2018 |website=BBC Sport |accessdate=22 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/c-palace-vs-liverpool/390771 |title=Crystal Palace 0\u20132 Liverpool: James Milner and Sadio Mane see off 10-man Eagles |publisher=Sky Sports |accessdate=22 September 2018}}</ref> Van Dijk received the [[2018\u201319 Liverpool F.C. season#Liverpool Standard Chartered Player of the Month award|Liverpool Standard Chartered Player of the Month]] award for his performances in August.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/316051-virgil-van-dijk-standard-chartered-player-of-the-month |title=Virgil van Dijk named Standard Chartered Player of the Month |publisher=Liverpool F.C. |accessdate=22 September 2018}}</ref> On 2 December, Van Dijk was awarded an assist for the winning goal in a [[Merseyside derby|derby]] match against city rivals Everton. Liverpool won 1\u20130 thanks to Divock Origi's 96th-minute goal, set up by a Van Dijk volley and a subsequent error from Everton goalkeeper [[Jordan Pickford]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/blog/the-toe-poke/65/post/3716494/liverpools-virgil-van-dijk-gets-assist-vs-everton-despite-ball-hitting-crossbar-twice |title=Van Dijk gets 'assist' despite ball hitting crossbar TWICE |date=3 December 2018 |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=21 December 2018}}</ref> The Dutchman was ultimately awarded the [[Professional Footballers' Association|PFA]] Player of the Month for November 2018.<ref name=\"LFCPFA\">{{cite web |url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/327733-virgil-van-dijk-pfa-player-of-the-month |title=Van Dijk wins PFA Player of the Month award |author=Carroll, James |publisher=Liverpool F.C. |date=3 December 2018 |accessdate=21 December 2018}}</ref> On 21 December, Van Dijk scored his first goal in the Premier League for Liverpool in a 2\u20130 away win against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref name=\"Guardian\">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/dec/21/wolves-liverpool-premier-league-match-report |title=Liverpool's Mohamed Salah and Virgil van Dijk put Wolves in their place |last=James |first=Stuart |work=The Guardian |date=21 December 2018 |accessdate=22 December 2018}}</ref> The Dutchman continued his impressive form in the 2018\u201319 season by winning the Premier League Player of the Month prize for December 2018.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Matchett |first1=Karl |title=Liverpool scoop double Manager and Player of the Month awards for December |url=https://www.thisisanfield.com/2019/01/liverpool-scoop-double-manager-and-player-of-the-month-awards-for-impressive-december-form/ |website=thisisanfield.com |publisher=Soccer Publishing Limited|accessdate=20 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 February 2019, Van Dijk scored twice in a 5&ndash;0 win against [[Watford F.C.|Watford]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/liverpool-vs-watford/391033 |title=Liverpool 5-0 Watford |work=Sky Sports |accessdate=28 February 2019}}</ref> The following month, he scored once - his first goal in the Champions League for the club - and assisted another in a 3\u20131 win over [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]]. In doing so, he became the first player since [[Craig Bellamy]] in 2007 to score and assist a goal for Liverpool in a knock-out stage match away from home in the competition.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.caughtoffside.com/2019/03/13/liverpools-van-dijk-matches-bellamy-vs-barcelona-stat/|title=Virgil van Dijk does something no Liverpool player has managed for 12 years|publisher=CaughtOffside|last=Brus|first=Mark|date=14 March 2019|accessdate=14 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 April, he was one of six players nominated for the [[PFA Players' Player of the Year]] award alongside teammate [[Sadio Man\u00e9]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2019/04/20/pfa-player-yearvirgil-van-dijk-raheem-sterling-lead-way-six/|title=PFA Player of the Year: Virgil van Dijk and Raheem Sterling lead the way in six-man shortlist|publisher=The Telegraph|date=20 April 2019|accessdate=20 April 2019}}</ref> Four days later, he was named in the [[PFA Team of the Year]] alongside Liverpool teammates, [[Trent Alexander-Arnold]], Man\u00e9 and [[Andrew Robertson]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thepfa.com/news/2019/4/25/premier-league-team-of-the-year|title=PFA Premier League Team of the Year|publisher=The Player's Football Association|date=25 April 2019|accessdate=25 April 2019}}</ref> On 28 April 2019, he was named the [[PFA Players' Player of the Year|PFA Player of the Year]].<ref name=\"BBC 280419\">{{cite web |title=Virgil van Dijk and Vivianne Miedema win PFA player of the year awards |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48065752 |website=BBC Sport |accessdate=29 April 2019 |date=28 April 2019}}</ref> Following Liverpool's 2\u20130 victory over [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham]] in the [[2019 UEFA Champions League Final]] on 1 June, Van Dijk was named [[UEFA]]'s ''Man of the match''.<ref name=\"MOTM\">{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2019/matches/round=2000984/match=2025486/postmatch/report/ |title=Liverpool beat Tottenham to win sixth European Cup |website=UEFA.com |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |date=1 June 2019 |access-date=1 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== 2019\u201320 season ====\n[[File:Liverpool vs. Chelsea, UEFA Super Cup 2019-08-14 33 (cropped).jpg|200px|thumb|Van Dijk playing for Liverpool against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]]]\nIn August 2019, Van Dijk won UEFA player of the year award. On 2 September 2019, he was shortlisted in the final three of the best FIFA football awards.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.stroudnewsandjournal.co.uk/sport/national/17875102.van-dijk-take-messi-ronaldo-fifa-player-year/|title=Van Dijk to take on Messi and Ronaldo again for FIFA player of the year| date= 2 September 2019| accessdate=2 September 2019|work=Stroud News}}</ref> On 23 September 2019, he was voted runner up in [[The Best FIFA Men's Player]] and into the FIFA [[The_Best_FIFA_Football_Awards_2019#FIFA_FIFPro_Men's_World11|FIFpro Men's World 11]].<ref name= FIFA2019result>{{cite_web|url=https://img.fifa.com/image/upload/itqmjfv2sfevdiib4psc.pdf|title=Final Ranking the best FIFA Football awards|access-date=24 September 2019|publisher=FIFA}}</ref><ref name=FIFA2019vote>{{cite_web|url=https://img.fifa.com/image/upload/z0gygcuwnxuz6pimfuhm.pdf|title=Voting breakdown in the best Fifa Men's player 2019|access-date=24 September 2019|publisher=FIFA}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.stroudnewsandjournal.co.uk/sport/national/17922187.rapinoe-calls-change-wins-big-alongside-messi-klopp/|title=Rapinoe calls for change as she wins big alongside Messi and Klopp| date=23 September 2019| accessdate=23 September 2019|work=Stroud News}}</ref> In October 2019, Van Dijk was shortlisted as one in 30 football players for the [[Ballon d'Or]].<ref>{{cite_web|first=Brendan|last= Hodrien|url=https://www.rousingthekop.com/2019/10/22/seven-liverpool-players-up-for-ballon-dor-as-reds-dominate-the-shortlist/|title=Seven Liverpool players up for Ballon d'Or as Reds dominate the shortlist|date=22 October 2019| accessdate=22 October 2019|website=Rousing The Kop}}</ref> At the event in December, he finished runner-up behind [[Lionel Messi]].<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.manisteenews.com/sports/article/US-soccer-star-Rapinoe-wins-Ballon-d-Or-14876298.php|title=Megan Rapinoe, Lionel Messi win Ballon d\u2019Or awards|accessdate=2 December 2019|website=News Manistee Advocate|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203150930/https://www.manisteenews.com/sports/article/US-soccer-star-Rapinoe-wins-Ballon-d-Or-14876298.php|archive-date=3 December 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 21 December 2019, after missing the semi-final of the [[2019 FIFA Club World Cup]] with illness, Van Dijk played in the [[2019 FIFA Club World Cup Final|final]] against [[Clube de Regatas do Flamengo|Flamengo]] with Liverpool winning the trophy for the first time in the club\u2019s history.<ref name=\"FIFA Final\">{{cite news |url=https://www.fifa.com/clubworldcup/news/firmino-writes-liverpool-into-club-world-cup-history |title=Firmino writes Liverpool into Club World Cup history |website=FIFA.com |publisher=F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Football Association |date=21 December 2019 |access-date=21 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Harry|last=Poole|title=Firmino winner seals Club World Cup win |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50869633|accessdate=22 December 2019 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> \n\nVan Dijk received further recognition following the turn of the year, when he was named in the 2019 [[UEFA Team of the Year]].<ref name=UTOTY2019>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2637433.html|title=UEFA.com fans' Team of the Year 2019 revealed|publisher=UEFA|date=15 January 2020|accessdate=15 January 2020}}</ref> On 19 January 2020, Van Dijk scored his first [[Liverpool F.C.\u2013Manchester United F.C. rivalry|North-West Derby]] goal against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in Liverpool\u2019s 2\u20130 win at Anfield in the Premier League.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2020/01/19/liverpool-vs-manchester-united-premier-league-live-score-latest/|title=Liverpool brush Manchester United aside in breathless contest to go 16 points clear at the top of the table|last=Burt|first=Jason|date=19 January 2020|work=The Telegraph|access-date=20 January 2020|last2=Tweedale|first2=Alistair|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51080695|title=Liverpool 2-0 Manchester United: Virgil van Dijk and Mo Salah goals secure win |publisher=BBC Sport |date=19 January 2020 |access-date=20 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nVan Dijk made his full international debut for [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] on 10 October 2015, in a 2\u20131 victory away from home against [[Kazakhstan national football team|Kazakhstan]] in a [[UEFA Euro 2016]] qualifier.<ref>{{cite web |title=Successful Saturday for Saints stars |url=https://southamptonfc.com/news/2015-10-10/successful-saturday-for-saints-stars |publisher=Southampton F.C. |date=10 October 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe was awarded the [[captain (association football)|captain]]cy of his country by manager [[Ronald Koeman]] on 22 March 2018,<ref>{{cite web|title=Van Dijk named new Netherlands captain |first=Daniel |last=Karell |date=22 March 2018 |accessdate=22 March 2018 |publisher=NBC Sports |url=http://soccer.nbcsports.com/2018/03/22/van-dijk-named-new-netherlands-captain/}}</ref> and his first match as captain was a 1\u20130 home friendly defeat by [[England national football team|England]] the next day.<ref>{{cite web|title=Netherlands 0\u20131 England |first=Phil |last=McNulty |date=23 March 2018 |accessdate=24 March 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/43380175}}</ref> On 26 March, he scored his first international goal to conclude a 3\u20130 win over European champions [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] at the [[Stade de Gen\u00e8ve]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Soccer \u2013 Portugal suffer first-half collapse in 3\u20130 loss to Dutch |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-friendly-por-ned/soccer-portugal-suffer-first-half-collapse-in-3-0-loss-to-dutch-idUKKBN1H22S7 |accessdate=26 March 2018 |agency=Reuters |date=26 March 2018}}</ref> On 13 October, he scored in a 3\u20130 win over [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014 World Cup]] champions [[Germany national football team|Germany]] in the [[2018\u201319 UEFA Nations League|UEFA Nations League]].<ref>{{Cite web  |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45851123 |title=Netherlands 3\u20130 Germany: Liverpool's Virgil van Dijk and Georginio Wijnaldum score for hosts |date=13 October 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=13 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nVan Dijk is a physically strong, right-footed [[centre-back]], who usually features on the left-hand side of central defence, although he can also play as a right-sided centre-back.<ref name=\"Best Defender-sportbible\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.sportbible.com/football/reactions-take-a-bow-news-virgil-van-dijk-voted-the-best-defender-in-world-football-20190316|title=Virgil Van Dijk Voted The Best Defender In World Football|date=16 March 2019|website=www.sportbible.com|access-date=20 April 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"best defender-sky\"/><ref name=NMcG>{{cite web|title=Virgil van Dijk 'can be a great' as Liverpool agree to pay \u00a375m for defender |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40730793 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 December 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> He is gifted with pace,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/1004040/watch-virgil-van-dijk-burns-premier-league-faster-player-in-a-sprint-liverpool-wolves/ |title=Watch: Virgil van Dijk burns \u2018Premier League\u2019s faster player\u2019 in a sprint |publisher=Fox Sports Asia |last1=Rangarajan |first1=Aditya |date=22 December 2018 |accessdate=3 June 2019 }}</ref> good technique, and an eye for goal, and is an effective [[Direct free kick|set-piece taker]]. Regarding his ability, former Celtic teammate [[Kris Commons]] commented that Van Dijk was \"comfortable on the ball\", also noting that \"He had good technique and a wonderful right foot. He was good on set-pieces, some of the free-kicks he scored for Celtic are absolute wonders. He could read the game well. He had an aura about him, a confidence, because I think he knew he was good.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/story-telling/15117/11684250/how-virgil-van-dijk-became-the-premier-leagues-top-defender |title=How Virgil van Dijk became the best |publisher=Sky Sports |last1=Bate |first1=Adam |accessdate=3 June 2019 }}</ref>\n\nNeil McGuinness, senior scout at Celtic when Van Dijk was signed, called him \"everything you would want if you could create a profile of the ideal central defender\", praising him as a \"very smooth ball-playing defender\" who possesses aerial prowess, skills from dead ball situations, and \"strong leadership qualities\", while commenting that since his move to England, he is \"more tactically aware now [...] his anticipation and timing has improved and he is a lot more of an all-rounder\".<ref name=NMcG/> McGuinness believes Van Dijk's \"biggest problem\" is that he \"can switch off when the game is comfortable\".<ref name=NMcG/>\n\nIn a 2019 interview with ''[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]'', when [[Lionel Messi]] was asked why Van Dijk was so difficult to beat, the Argentine responded: \"He is a defender who knows how to judge his timing and wait for the right moment to challenge or jockey [the attacker]. He is very fast and big, but he has a lot of agility for his height. He is fast because of its [sic] great stride, and he is impressive both in defence and attack because he scores lots of goals.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/barcelona/2019/10/17/5da81c0122601d1b308b458c.html |title=Messi: The body rules and I have to take more care of myself than before |website=www.Marca.com|last1=Gallardo |first1=Juan Ignacio |last2=Rojo |first2=Luis F. |date=17 October 2019 |accessdate=17 October 2019 }}</ref> That same year, [[Paul Merson]] described Van Dijk as \"the best in the world, and I think by a long way, as a defensive centre-half.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11669/11659594/virgil-van-dijk-the-best-defender-in-the-world-says-paul-merson |title=Virgil van Dijk the best defender in the world, says Paul Merson |publisher=Sky Sports |last1=Merson |first1=Paul |date=9 March 2019 |accessdate=8 April 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==Sponsorship==\nVan Dijk features as the cover star of the champions edition of [[EA Sports]]' [[FIFA (video game series)|''FIFA'']] video game ''[[FIFA 20]]''.<ref>{{cite news |title=Virgil van Dijk to be EA SPORTS' FIFA 20 Champions Edition cover star |url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/announcements/357944-virgil-van-dijk-fifa-20-champions-edition-cover-star |accessdate=26 July 2019 |work=LiverpoolFC.com}}</ref> He is endorsed by sportswear company [[Nike football|Nike]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/Companies/bmR0I1uUxIr0zZjXAlEAII/Nike-gains-a-step-on-Adidas-in-competition-for-top-football.html|title=Nike gains a step on Adidas in competition for top football stars|last=Weiss|first=Richard|date=2018-01-26|website=www.livemint.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-05}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nVan Dijk commonly uses only his first name on the kit. According to his uncle Steven, this is because of a feud with his father.<ref>{{cite web |title=Here Is Why Virgil van Dijk Only Uses His First Name On Kit |url=https://www.footyheadlines.com/2019/03/here-is-why-virgil-van-dijk-only-uses-first-name-on-kit.html |website=Footy Headlines |accessdate=18 March 2019 |date=18 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 11 March 2020}}\n\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|National Cup{{efn|Includes [[KNVB Cup]], [[Scottish Cup]], [[FA Cup]]}}\n!colspan=2|League Cup{{efn|Includes [[Scottish League Cup]], [[EFL Cup|League Cup/EFL Cup]]}}\n!colspan=2|Europe\n!colspan=2|Other\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[FC Groningen|Groningen]]\n|[[2010\u201311 Eredivisie|2010\u201311]]<ref name=Soccerway/>\n|[[Eredivisie]]\n|5||2||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||5||2\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Eredivisie|2011\u201312]]<ref name=Soccerway/>\n|Eredivisie\n|23||3||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||24||3\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Eredivisie|2012\u201313]]<ref name=Soccerway>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/virgil-van-dijk/188624/ |title=V. Van Dijk: Summary |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=21 December 2018}}</ref>\n|Eredivisie\n|34||2||3||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||37||2\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!62||7||4||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||66||7\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]\n|[[2013\u201314 Celtic F.C. season|2013\u201314]]<ref name=sb1314>{{soccerbase season|59442|2013|accessdate=29 September 2016}}</ref>\n|[[Scottish Premiership]]\n|36||5||2||0||1||0||8{{efn|name=UCL|Appearances in [[UEFA Champions League]]}}||0||colspan=2|\u2014||47||5\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 Celtic F.C. season|2014\u201315]]<ref name=sb1415>{{soccerbase season|59442|2014|accessdate=29 September 2016}}</ref>\n|Scottish Premiership\n|35||4||5||4||4||0||14{{efn|Six appearances in UEFA Champions League; eight appearances in [[UEFA Europa League]]}}||2||colspan=2|\u2014||58||10\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 Celtic F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref name=sb1516/>\n|Scottish Premiership\n|5||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||5{{efn|name=UCL}}||0||colspan=2|\u2014||10||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!76||9||7||4||5||0||27||2||colspan=2|\u2014||115||15\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]]\n|[[2015\u201316 Southampton F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref name=sb1516>{{soccerbase season|59442|2015|accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n|[[Premier League]]\n|34||3||1||0||3||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||38||3\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Southampton F.C. season|2016\u201317]]<ref name=sb1617>{{soccerbase season|59442|2016|accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|21||1||1||1||2||0||6{{efn|Appearances in UEFA Europa League}}||2||colspan=2|\u2014||30||4\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 Southampton F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=sb1718/>\n|Premier League\n|12||0||colspan=2|\u2014||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||12||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!67||4||2||1||5||0||6||2||colspan=2|\u2014||80||7\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]\n|[[2017\u201318 Liverpool F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=sb1718>{{soccerbase season|59442|2017|accessdate=12 August 2018}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|14||0||2||1||colspan=2|\u2014||6{{efn|name=UCL}}||0||colspan=2|\u2014||22||1\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 Liverpool F.C. season|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{soccerbase season|59442|2018|accessdate=10 August 2019}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|38||4||0||0||0||0||12{{efn|name=UCL}}||2||colspan=2|\u2014||50||6\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 Liverpool F.C. season|2019\u201320]]<ref>{{soccerbase season|59442|2019|accessdate=19 January 2020}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|29||4||1||0||0||0||8{{efn|name=UCL}}||0||3{{efn|One appearance in [[FA Community Shield]], one appearance in [[UEFA Super Cup]], one appearance in [[FIFA Club World Cup]]|name=|group=}}||0||41||4\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!81||8||3||1||0||0||26||2||3||0||113||11\n|-\n!colspan=3|Career total\n!286||28||16||6||10||0||59||6||3||0||374||40\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\n===International===\n{{updated|match played 16 November 2019}}<ref name=NFT>{{NFT player |id=60815 |name=Van Dijk, Virgil |accessdate=10 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|+ Appearances and goals by national team and year\n|-\n\n!National team!!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=5|[[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]]\n|2015||3||0\n|-\n|2016||9||0\n|-\n|2017||4||0\n|-\n|2018||8||3\n|-\n|2019||9||1\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total||33||4\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n: ''As of match played on 9 September 2019. Netherlands score listed first, score column indicates score after each Van Dijk goal.''<ref name=NFT/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ International goals by date, venue, cap, opponent, score, result and competition\n|-\n!scope=col|No.\n!scope=col|Date\n!scope=col|Venue\n!scope=col|Cap\n!scope=col|Opponent\n!scope=col|Score\n!scope=col|Result\n!scope=col|Competition\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|1\n|26 March 2018||[[Stade de Gen\u00e8ve]], Geneva, Switzerland||align=center|18||{{fb|POR}}||align=center|3\u20130||align=center|3\u20130||[[Exhibition game#Association football|Friendly]]\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|2\n|13 October 2018||[[Johan Cruyff Arena]], Amsterdam, Netherlands||align=center|22||rowspan=2|{{fb|GER}}||align=center|1\u20130||align=center|3\u20130||rowspan=2|[[2018\u201319 UEFA Nations League A]]\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|3\n|19 November 2018||[[Arena AufSchalke]], Gelsenkirchen, Germany||align=center|24||align=center|2\u20132||align=center|2\u20132\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|4\n|21 March 2019||[[De Kuip]], Rotterdam, Netherlands||align=center|25||{{fb|BLR}}||align=center|4\u20130||align=center|4\u20130||[[UEFA Euro 2020 qualification]]\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Celtic'''\n*[[Scottish Premiership]]: [[2013\u201314 Scottish Premiership|2013\u201314]], [[2014\u201315 Scottish Premiership|2014\u201315]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/virgil-van-dijk_prs276965/person.shtml |title=Virgil van Dijk |publisher=Eurosport |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Scottish League Cup]]: [[2014\u201315 Scottish League Cup|2014\u201315]]<ref name=2015SLC/>\n\n'''Liverpool'''\n*[[UEFA Champions League]]: [[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League|2018\u201319]];<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48368443 |title=Tottenham Hotspur 0\u20132 Liverpool |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=1 June 2019 |accessdate=1 June 2019}}</ref> runner-up: [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League|2017\u201318]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44258022 |title=Real Madrid 3\u20131 Liverpool |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=26 May 2018 |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA Super Cup]]: [[2019 UEFA Super Cup|2019]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49332825 |title=Liverpool 2\u20132 Chelsea |first=Gary |last=Rose |website=BBC Sport |date=14 August 2019 |accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref>\n*[[FIFA Club World Cup]]: [[2019 FIFA Club World Cup|2019]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50869633 |title=Liverpool 1\u20130 Flamengo |first=Harry |last=Poole |website=BBC Sport |date=21 December 2019 |accessdate=21 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Netherlands'''\n*[[UEFA Nations League]] runner-up: [[2018\u201319 UEFA Nations League|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48191922 |title=Portugal 1\u20132 Netherlands |first=Shamoon |last=Hafez |website=BBC Sport |date=9 June 2019 |accessdate=25 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[PFA Players' Player of the Year]]: [[2018\u201319 Premier League#Annual awards|2018\u201319]]<ref name=\"BBC 280419\"/>\n*[[PFA Team of the Year]]: [[PFA Team of the Year (2010s)#Premier League 10|2018\u201319 Premier League]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/48028713|title=PFA Team of the Year: Paul Pogba, Raheem Sterling and Sadio Mane included in side|website=BBC Sport|date=25 April 2019|accessdate=25 April 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Professional Footballers' Association|PFA Player of the Month]]: November 2018<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/327733-virgil-van-dijk-pfa-player-of-the-month |title=Van Dijk wins PFA Player of the Month award |publisher=Liverpool F.C. |accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Premier League Player of the Season]]: [[2018\u201319 Premier League#Annual awards|2018\u201319]]<ref name=PremProfile>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/players/5140/Virgil-van-Dijk/overview |title=Virgil van Dijk: Overview |publisher=Premier League |accessdate=21 December 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Premier League Player of the Month]]: [[2018\u201319 Premier League#Monthly awards|December 2018]]<ref name=PremProfile/>\n*[[UEFA Men's Player of the Year Award]]: 2018\u201319<ref name=\"UEFAMPOTY19\"/>\n*[[UEFA Club Football Awards|UEFA Defender of the Season]]: [[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League#Defender of the season|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2618579.html?iv=true|title=Virgil van Dijk: Champions League Defender of the Season|date=29 August 2019|publisher=UEFA|accessdate=29 August 2019}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA Team of the Year]]: [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2018|2018]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2589223.html |title=UEFA.com fans' Team of the Year 2018 revealed |publisher=UEFA |date=11 January 2019 |accessdate=11 January 2019}}</ref> [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2019|2019]]<ref name=UTOTY2019/>\n*UEFA Champions League Squad of the Season: [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League#Squad of the Season|2017\u201318]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2560100.html |title=UEFA Champions League Squad of the Season |publisher=UEFA |date=27 May 2018 |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref> [[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League#Squad of the Season|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2607890.html |title=UEFA Champions League Squad of the Season |publisher=UEFA.com |date=2 June 2019 |accessdate=2 June 2019}}</ref>\n*UEFA Nations League Finals Team of the Tournament: [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals|2019]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/news/newsid=2607717.html |title=UEFA Nations League Finals: Team of the Tournament |website=UEFA.com |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |date=10 June 2019 |access-date=11 June 2019}}</ref>\n*[[The Best FIFA Men's Player]]: [[The Best FIFA Football Awards 2019#The Best FIFA Men's Player|2019]] (2nd place)<ref name= FIFA2019result />\n*[[Liverpool Player of the Season Awards|Liverpool Fans Player of the Season Award]]: [[2018\u201319 Liverpool F.C. season|2018\u201319]]<ref name = \"lfc 2019\">{{cite news |title=Revealed: The LFC Players' Awards 2019 winners |url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/announcements/351626-revealed-the-lfc-players-awards-2019-winners |accessdate=31 May 2019 |work=Liverpool FC |date=27 May 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Liverpool Player of the Season Awards|Liverpool Players' Player of the Season Award]]: 2018\u201319<ref name = \"lfc 2019\"/>\n*[[Southampton F.C. Player of the Season|Southampton Player of the Season]]: [[2015\u201316 Southampton F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://southamptonfc.com/news/2016-05-11/van-dijk-the-big-winner-at-saints-player-awards |title=Van Dijk the big winner at Saints' Player Awards |publisher=Southampton F.C. |date=11 May 2016 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n*[[PFA Scotland Team of the Year]]: [[PFA Scotland Team of the Year#Premiership|2013\u201314]],<ref name=\"1314PFA\" /> [[PFA Scotland Team of the Year#Premiership 2|2014\u201315]]<ref name=\"1415PFA\" />\n*[[Celtic F.C. Player of The Year|Celtic FC Players' Player of the Year]]: [[Celtic F.C. Player of the Year#2013\u201314|2013\u201314]]<ref>{{cite web| title=Champions celebrate at Awards night | url=http://www.celticfc.net/news/5816 | publisher=Celtic FC | date=4 May 2014 | accessdate=21 May 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Goal (website)#Goal 50|Goal 50]]: 2018\u201319<ref>{{cite news |title=Virgil van Dijk and Megan Rapinoe win Goal 50 best player awards |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/virgil-van-dijk-and-megan-rapinoe-win-goal-50-best-player/qgmapfu14jct10sa5vm5wpsvw |accessdate=12 November 2019 |work=Goal.com |date=12 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[FIFPro#FIFA FIFPro Men's World11|FIFA FIFPro World11]]: [[The Best FIFA Football Awards 2019#FIFA FIFPro World11|2019]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/the-best-fifa-football-awards/fifa-fifpro-mens-world11/ |title=World 11: FIFA FIFPro Men's World11 - Winner |publisher=FIFA.com |date=23 September 2019}}</ref>\n*[[International Federation of Football History & Statistics#IFFHS Men's World Team|IFFHS Men's World Team]]: 2019<ref>{{cite web |url=https://iffhs.de/iffhs-awards-the-iffhs-men-world-team-of-the-year-2019/ |title=IFFHS AWARDS 2019 \u2013 THE IFFHS MEN WORLD TEAM OF THE YEAR 2019 |work=IFFHS |date=30 November 2019 |accessdate=30 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Football Supporters' Federation]] Player of the Year: [[Football Supporters' Federation#FSF Player of the Year Award|2019]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Virgil Van Dijk named Football Supporters\u2019 Association men\u2019s player of the year |url=https://www.independent.ie/sport/soccer/virgil-van-dijk-named-football-supporters-association-mens-player-of-the-year-38790875.html|date=12 January 2020 |accessdate=12 January 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Ballon d'Or]]: [[2019 Ballon d'Or|2019]] (2nd place)<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.francefootball.fr/news/Virgil-van-dijk-2e-du-ballon-d-or-france-football-2019/1086009 |title=Ranking of the Ballon d'Or France Football 2019: Virgil van Dijk is 2nd |newspaper=France Football |date=2 December 2019 |accessdate=3 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*[https://www.liverpoolfc.com/team/first-team/player/virgil-van-dijk Profile] at the Liverpool F.C. website\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{Liverpool F.C. squad}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards\n| bg = gold\n| fg = navy\n| list1 = \n{{2013\u201314 PFA Scotland Scottish Premiership Team of the Year}}\n{{2014\u201315 PFA Scotland Scottish Premiership Team of the Year}}\n{{2018\u201319 Premier League PFA Team of the Year}}\n{{2018 UEFA Team of the Year}}\n{{2019 UEFA Team of the Year}}\n{{2019 UEFA Nations League Finals Team of the Tournament}}\n{{Southampton F.C. Player of the Season}}\n{{Liverpool F.C. Player of the Season}}\n{{PFA Players' Player of the Year}}\n{{Premier League Player of the Season}}\n{{UEFA Men's Player of the Year}}\n{{UEFA Club Football Awards}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dijk, Virgil Van}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Dutch people of Surinamese descent]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Breda]]\n[[Category:Dutch footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Willem II (football club) players]]\n[[Category:FC Groningen players]]\n[[Category:Celtic F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Southampton F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Liverpool F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Eredivisie players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Professional Football League players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Champions League winning players]]\n[[Category:Netherlands youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Netherlands under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Netherlands international footballers]]\n[[Category:Dutch expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Dutch expatriate sportspeople in Scotland]]\n[[Category:Dutch expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Scotland]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Dutch association football player}}\n{{EngvarB|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Dutch name|van Dijk|Dijk}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Virgil van Dijk\n| image = 20160604 AUT NED 8876 (cropped).jpg\n| image_size = 235\n| caption = Van Dijk lining up for the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in 2016\n| fullname = Virgil van Dijk<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/84136 |title=Squads for 2016/17 Premier League confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=1 September 2016 |accessdate=11 September 2016}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1991|7|8|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.11v11.com/players/virgil-van-dijk-247921/ |title=Virgil Van Dijk |website=11v11.com |publisher=AFS Enterprises |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Breda]], Netherlands\n| height = 1.93 m<ref>{{cite web |url=https://southamptonfc.com/first-team/virgil-van-dijk |title=Virgil van Dijk |publisher=Southampton F.C. |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170311031725/https://southamptonfc.com/first-team/virgil-van-dijk |archivedate=11 March 2017 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| position = [[Centre-back]]\n| currentclub = [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]\n| clubnumber = 4\n| youthyears1 = 2009\u20132010\n| youthclubs1 = [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]]\n| youthyears2 = 2010\u20132011\n| youthclubs2 = [[FC Groningen|Groningen]]\n| years1 = 2011\u20132013\n| clubs1 = [[FC Groningen|Groningen]]\n| caps1 = 62\n| goals1 = 7\n| years2 = 2013\u20132015\n| clubs2 = [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]\n| caps2 = 76\n| goals2 = 9\n| years3 = 2015\u20132018\n| clubs3 = [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]]\n| caps3 = 67\n| goals3 = 4\n| years4 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs4 = [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]\n| caps4 = 81\n| goals4 = 8<!-- This section is for league goals only.-->\n| nationalyears1 = 2011\n| nationalteam1 = [[Netherlands national under-19 football team|Netherlands U19]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 1\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2011\u20132013\n| nationalteam2 = [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|Netherlands U21]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 3\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2015\u2013\n| nationalteam3 = [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 33\n| nationalgoals3 = 4\n| medaltemplates = {{Medal|Sport|Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{Medal|Country|{{fb|NED}}}}\n{{Medal|Comp|[[UEFA Nations League]]}}\n{{Medal|Silver|[[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals|2019 Portugal]]|}}\n| club-update = 14:24, 7 March 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 08:54, 20 November 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Virgil van Dijk''' ({{IPA-nl|v\u0251n \u02c8d\u025bik}}; born 8 July 1991) is a Dutch professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for English {{English football updater|Liverpoo}} club [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] and [[captain (association football)|captains]] the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]]. Considered to be one of the best defenders in the world, he is known for his strength, leadership and aerial ability.<ref name=\"Best Defender-sportbible\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.sportbible.com/football/reactions-take-a-bow-news-virgil-van-dijk-voted-the-best-defender-in-world-football-20190316|title=Virgil Van Dijk Voted The Best Defender In World Football|date=16 March 2019|website=www.sportbible.com|access-date=20 April 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"best defender-sky\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11669/11659594/virgil-van-dijk-the-best-defender-in-the-world-says-paul-merson|title=Virgil van Dijk the best defender in the world, says Paul Merson|website=Sky Sports|access-date=20 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2618579.html|title=Virgil van Dijk: Champions League Defender of the Season|last=UEFA.com|website=UEFA.com|language=en|access-date=2019-09-01}}</ref> In 2019 he was named the [[UEFA Men's Player of the Year Award|UEFA Men's Player of the Year]], and finished runner-up for the [[Ballon d'Or]] and [[The Best FIFA Football Awards 2019|The Best FIFA Men's Player]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/the-best-fifa-football-awards/best-fifa-mens-player/|title=The Best FIFA Men's Player|website=www.fifa.com|accessdate=2 September 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"UEFAMPOTY19\">{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2618573.html|title=Virgil van Dijk wins UEFA Men's Player of the Year award|publisher=UEFA|accessdate=29 August 2019|date=29 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nAfter beginning his professional career with [[FC Groningen|Groningen]], Van Dijk moved to [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] in 2013, where he won the [[Scottish Premiership]] and was named in the [[PFA Scotland Team of the Year]] in both of his seasons with the club, also winning the [[Scottish League Cup]] in the latter. In September 2015, he joined Premier League side [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] before signing for Liverpool in January 2018 for \u00a375&nbsp;million, a [[List of most expensive association football transfers|world record transfer fee]] for a defender at the time.<ref name=BBCLiverpool/> Van Dijk was involved in reaching the [[2018 UEFA Champions League Final]] during his first spring at Liverpool. In his first full season at the club Van Dijk was named the [[PFA Players' Player of the Year|PFA Player of the Year]] and the [[Premier League Player of the Season]] for the 2018\u201319 season.<ref name=\"BBC 280419\"/><ref name=\"PL POTS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/1214766|title=Van Dijk named EA SPORTS Player of the Season|publisher=Premier League|accessdate=12 May 2019|date=12 May 2019}}</ref> Van Dijk starred as Liverpool won the [[2019 UEFA Champions League Final]] where he was named man of the match.<ref name=\"MOTM\"/> The following season he played in the club\u2019s victorious [[2019 FIFA Club World Cup Final]].<ref name=\"FIFA Final\"/>\n\nVan Dijk made his international debut for the Netherlands in 2015 and became captain of his country in 2018. In 2018, he scored his first international goal in a 3\u20130 win over European champions [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]]. He later captained them to the inaugural [[2019 UEFA Nations League Final]] where they finished runners-up.\n\n==Club career==\n===Early life and career===\nVan Dijk was born in [[Breda]] to a [[Dutch people|Dutch]] father and a [[Surinamese people|Surinamese]] mother.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.celticfc.net/newsstory?item=4174 |title=News |publisher=Celtic F.C. |accessdate=16 May 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029210911/http://www.celticfc.net/newsstory?item=4174 |archivedate=29 October 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Growing up he would play football wherever he could \u2013 on the streets, in concrete cages, and eventually Saturday morning matches.<ref>{{cite news |title=Virgil van Dijk exclusive: \u201cI\u2019m not going to lie, I was pretty scared \u2013 I could have died\u201d |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/virgil-van-dijk-exclusive-im-not-going-lie-i-was-pretty-scared-i-could-have-died#TWOCEsmY6Jcvxwi7.99 |accessdate=5 November 2019 |work=Four Four Two}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Virgil van Dijk: Birthplace of Dreams {{!}} Nike|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O8d_VA6eE2M|language=en|access-date=2019-12-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nike.com/il/football/virgil-van-dijk-birthplace-of-dreams|title=Virgil van Dijk|website=Nike.com|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-12-05}}</ref> He combined his time playing at the [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]] academy with a part-time job as a dishwasher.<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/47283936|title=Virgil van Dijk wants to be 'a legend of Liverpool' - in-depth wide-ranging BBC interview|date=21 February 2019|website=BBC Sport}}</ref><ref name=espn>{{cite news|url=http://africa.espn.com/football/club/liverpool/364/blog/post/3824468/virgil-van-dijk-is-the-best-player-in-the-premier-league-how-the-dutch-defender-became-liverpools-leader|title=Virgil van Dijk is the best player in the Premier League: how the Dutch defender became Liverpool's leader|publisher=ESPN|last=Kuper|first=Simon|date=16 April 2019|accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref> Having previously and unsuccessfully featured as a right-back, Van Dijk was shifted into a central defensive position in 2008, aged 17, after he grew in height by around 18 centimetres.<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\"/><ref name=espn/> Despite the positional shift and Van Dijk's physical growth, Willem II's reserve manager at the time [[Edwin Hermans]] believed he had \"too many limitations\" which prevented him from breaking into the first team.<ref name=espn/> In 2010, he was scouted by former Dutch international [[Martin Koeman]], who was working for [[FC Groningen]] at the time, and he ended up completing a free transfer to the club in the same year.<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\"/><ref name=espn/>\n\n===Groningen===\n\nVan Dijk initially struggled to break into Groningen's first team with club staff believing he was \"overtired\" after extensive playing time with Willem II's academy and reserve sides.<ref name=espn/> He made his professional debut for the club on 1 May 2011, coming on as a 72nd-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Petter Andersson]] during a 4\u20132 victory against [[ADO Den Haag]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2011/05/01/netherlands/eredivisie/hfc-ado-den-haag/stichting-fc-groningen/941703/ |title=ADO Den Haag VS. Groningen 2\u20134 |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform group |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On 29 May, and against the same opposition, he made his first start for Groningen and scored his first professional goals, netting twice in a 5\u20131 win in a [[UEFA Europa League]] play-off match.<ref name=espn/>\n\nDuring the [[2011\u201312 Eredivisie]] season, Van Dijk made 23 league appearances for the [[Eredivisie]] team, and scored his first regular-season goal during the club's 6\u20130 victory over [[Feyenoord]] on 30 October 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soccerbox.com/blog/virgil-van-dijk-premier-league/ |title=Virgil van Dijk One of the Finest Centre-Backs in the Premier League |website=Soccer Box}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/152437/eredivisie-fc-groningen-feyenoord/ |title=Wedstrijd: FC Groningen \u2013 Feyenoord |website=FCUpdate.nl}}</ref> He suffered a personal setback during the campaign, however, as soon after his 20th birthday he was admitted to hospital with [[peritonitis]] and kidney poisoning. Van Dijk later revealed that he had been close to dying as a result of the medical emergency and that the hospital had even gone so far as to ask him to sign a \"sort of [[Will and testament|will]]\" in the event of his passing.<ref name=espn/>\n\nHe did, however, return to Groningen and continued to impress the following season. At the end of the campaign, and with Van Dijk having \"outgrown\" the club, he was offered to a number of bigger Eredivisie clubs, including [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], all of whom elected not to sign him.<ref name=espn/> Instead, in June 2013, he joined Scottish side [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]].<ref name=espn/>\n\n===Celtic===\n====2013\u201314 season====\nOn 21 June 2013, Van Dijk signed with [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] for a fee of around \u00a32.6&nbsp;million, on a four-year deal including a 10% selling-on fee for Groningen.<ref>{{cite news |title=Virgil van Dijk: Dutch defender joins Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/23004736 |website=BBC Sport |date=21 June 2013 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> He made his debut on 17 August, replacing [[Efe Ambrose]] for the final 13 minutes of a 2\u20130 [[Scottish Premiership]] win over [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]] at [[Pittodrie Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Keir |last=Murray |title=Aberdeen 0\u20132 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/23644812 |website=BBC Sport |date=17 August 2013 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> A week later, he made his first start, in a 2\u20132 draw with [[Inverness Caledonian Thistle F.C.|Inverness Caledonian Thistle]] at [[Celtic Park]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Celtic 2\u20132 Inverness CT |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/23737036 |website=BBC Sport |date=24 August 2013 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On 9 November, Van Dijk scored his first Celtic goals, heading one in each half of a 4\u20131 win against [[Ross County F.C.|Ross County]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Martin |last=Conaghan |title=Ross County 1\u20134 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/24783003 |website=BBC Sport |date=9 November 2013 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> After a solo run, he scored the only goal of a victory over [[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]] on 26 December.<ref>{{cite news |first=Andy |last=Campbell |title=St Johnstone 0\u20131 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/25442036 |website=BBC Sport |date=26 December 2013 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nVan Dijk scored again on 26 January 2014, in a 4\u20130 win versus [[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]] for Celtic's 11th consecutive league win.<ref>{{cite news |first=Keir |last=Murray |title=Hibernian 0\u20134 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/25798579 |website=BBC Sport |date=26 January 2014 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On 25 February, he was sent off after 13 minutes of an eventual 2\u20131 loss at Aberdeen, for a professional foul on [[Peter Pawlett]]; it was Celtic's first defeat of the season.<ref>{{cite news |first=Andrew |last=Southwick |title=Aberdeen 2\u20131 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/25892139 |website=BBC Sport |date=25 February 2014 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> With Celtic having already won the league, Van Dijk netted again on 7 May to put his team 3\u20131 up away to St Johnstone, in an eventual 3\u20133 draw.<ref>{{cite news |first=Cheri |last=Burns |title=St Johnstone 3\u20133 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/27216459 |website=BBC Sport |date=7 May 2014 |accessdate=17 October 2015}}</ref> He was one of three Celtic players named in the [[PFA Scotland Team of the Year]].<ref name=1314PFA>{{cite news |title=Celtic and Dundee United trios in SPFL Premiership team of year |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/27080030 |website=BBC Sport |date=18 April 2014 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> Van Dijk was nominated for the [[PFA Scotland Players' Player of the Year]] award,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://spfl.co.uk/news/article/pfa-player-of-year-nominees/ | title=PFA Player of the Year nominees | publisher=[[Scottish Professional Football League|SPFL]] | date=16 April 2014 | accessdate=12 May 2019}}</ref> but lost out to fellow Celtic player [[Kris Commons]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://spfl.co.uk/news/article/pfa-scotland-award-winners/ | title=PFA Scotland award winners | publisher=[[Scottish Professional Football League|SPFL]] | date=27 April 2014 | accessdate=12 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n====2014\u201315 season====\n[[File:Virgil van Dijk 2015.jpg|thumb|upright|Van Dijk playing for [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] in 2015]]\n\nOn 22 July 2014, Van Dijk and [[Teemu Pukki]] each scored twice in a 4\u20130 home win over [[Knattspyrnuf\u00e9lag Reykjav\u00edkur|KR]] in a [[UEFA Champions League]] qualifier, putting their team into the next round 5\u20130 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite news |first=Ben |last=Burrows |title=Celtic 4\u20130 KR Reykjavik: Hoops ease into next Champions League round in comfortable fashion |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/celtic-4-0-kr-reykjavik-hoops-3897700 |newspaper=Daily Mirror |location=London |date=22 July 2014 |accessdate=17 October 2015}}</ref> His first goal of the [[2014\u201315 Scottish Premiership|Premiership season]] came on 9 November, finishing from [[Stefan Johansen]]'s last-minute corner for a 2\u20131 win at Aberdeen.<ref>{{cite news |first=Colin |last=Moffat |title=Aberdeen 1\u20132 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/29868766 |website=BBC Sport |date=9 November 2014 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> Three weeks later, Van Dijk scored the first and last goals of Celtic's 4\u20130 win versus [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Heart of Midlothian]] in the fourth round of the [[Scottish Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Andrew |last=Southwick |title=Heart of Midlothian 0\u20134 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/30166217 |website=BBC Sport |date=30 November 2014 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> Four days after that, his sixth goal of the season was enough for victory in a home match against [[Glasgow]] neighbours [[Partick Thistle F.C.|Partick Thistle]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Richard |last=Wilson |title=Celtic 1\u20130 Partick Thistle |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/28647040 |website=BBC Sport |date=4 December 2014 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nVan Dijk was again on target on 21 January 2015, opening a 4\u20130 home win over [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Colin |last=Moffat |title=Celtic 4\u20130 Motherwell |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/30808448 |website=BBC Sport |date=21 January 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On 26 February, he was sent off in the 36th minute against [[Inter Milan]] for a foul on [[Mauro Icardi]], as Celtic lost 1\u20130 on the night, 4\u20133 on aggregate in the last 32 of the [[UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Craig |last=Swan |title=Inter 1 Celtic 0 (4\u20133 agg): Late strike finishes off battling ten-man Celtic and ends their Europa League run |url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-match-reports/inter-1-celtic-0-4-3-5239236 |newspaper=Daily Record |location=Glasgow |date=26 February 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> He was again sent off on 8 March in the Cup quarter-final away to [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] at [[Tannadice Park]], receiving a red card after eleven minutes for a confrontation with [[Calum Butcher]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Keir |last=Murray |title=Dundee United 1\u20131 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31680308 |website=BBC Sport |date=8 March 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> His suspension for the following week's [[2015 Scottish League Cup Final|Scottish League Cup Final]] was overturned on appeal, as was that of [[Paul Paton]], who was sent off when mistaken for Butcher.<ref>{{cite news |title=Van Dijk and Paton cleared to play in League Cup final |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31858622 |website=BBC Sport |date=12 March 2015 |accessdate=18 October 2015}}</ref> Van Dijk played the full 90 minutes of the final at [[Hampden Park]], which Celtic won 2\u20130.<ref name=2015SLC>{{cite news |first=Richard |last=Wilson |title=Dundee United 0\u20132 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31785677 |website=BBC Sport |date=15 March 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On 18 March, Celtic's third consecutive match against Dundee United, Van Dijk scored in the last minute to confirm a 4\u20130 win in a Cup replay.<ref>{{cite news |title=Celtic 4\u20130 Dundee United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31826157 |website=BBC Sport |date=18 March 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 April, Celtic contested the Cup semi-final against Inverness at Hampden, and Van Dijk opened the scoring with a free kick. After the dismissal of goalkeeper [[Craig Gordon]], Celtic fell 3\u20132, ending their chance of a [[Treble (association football)|treble]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Clive |last=Lindsay |title=Inverness Caledonian Thistle 3\u20132 Celtic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32089585 |website=BBC Sport |date=19 April 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> Three days later, again from a free kick, he confirmed a 2\u20131 win away to [[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Andrew |last=Southwick |title=Celtic 1\u20132 Dundee |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31827990 |website=BBC Sport |date=22 April 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> His team again won the league, and Van Dijk was included in the league's Team of the Season for the second consecutive campaign.<ref name=1415PFA>{{cite news |first=Gregor |last=Kyle |title=The SPFL dream team: PFA Scotland announce their teams of the year |url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/spfl-dream-team-pfa-scotland-5616035 |newspaper=Daily Record |location=Glasgow |date=1 May 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> He was again shortlisted for the PFA Scotland Players' Player award,<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32435212 | title=Celtic's Van Dijk & Johansen join Rooney & Stewart in award mix | website=BBC Sport | date=23 April 2015 | accessdate=12 May 2019}}</ref> but lost out to another teammate, this time [[Stefan Johansen]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32578058 | title=Stefan Johansen: Celtic midfielder named Scottish PFA player of the year |website=BBC Sport | date=3 May 2015 | accessdate=12 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nVan Dijk was reportedly \"considering his future\" in Glasgow after Celtic were knocked out of the [[2015\u201316 UEFA Champions League]] in the qualifying rounds to [[Malm\u00f6 FF|Malm\u00f6]] of Sweden.<ref>{{cite news |title=Virgil van Dijk: Celtic defender considers future after defeat |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34060123 |website=BBC Sport |date=26 August 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Southampton===\nOn 1 September 2015, Van Dijk signed a five-year contract with [[Premier League]] club [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]], managed by [[Ronald Koeman]], for a reported \u00a313&nbsp;million transfer fee.<ref>{{cite web |title=Saints complete deadline-day deal for van Dijk |url=https://southamptonfc.com/news/2015-09-01/saints-complete-deadline-day-deal-for-van-dijk |publisher=Southampton F.C. |date=1 September 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Virgil van Dijk: Southampton sign Celtic defender for \u00a313m |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34115519 |website=BBC Sport |date=1 September 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==== 2015\u201316 season ====\nHe made his debut for Southampton on 12 September in a 0\u20130 draw against [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] at [[The Hawthorns]].<ref name=\"sb1516\" /> Two weeks later, Van Dijk marked his third Premier League appearance with his first goal for the club, which came in the form of a header in the 11th minute to put Southampton in front, following a set-piece from [[James Ward-Prowse]] in a 3\u20131 home win over [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Saj |last=Chowdhury |title=Southampton 3\u20131 Swansea City |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34299542 |website=BBC Sport |date=26 August 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On 7 May 2016, Van Dijk signed a new six-year contract with the Saints.<ref>{{cite news |title=Virgil van Dijk: Dutch defender signs new six-year deal at Southampton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36236667 |website=BBC Sport |date=7 May 2016 |accessdate=8 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n==== 2016\u201317 season ====\nOn 22 January 2017, he was named team captain of Southampton, after the departure of [[Jos\u00e9 Fonte]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://southamptonfc.com/news/2017-01-22/claude-puel-captains-southampton-virgil-van-dijk-steven-davis |title=Puel confirms Saints' new captains |publisher=Southampton F.C. |date=22 January 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On the same day, he suffered an ankle injury against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Andy |last=Charles |title=Southampton's Virgil van Dijk out for at least two months with ankle injury |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11700/10753362/southamptons-virgil-van-dijk-out-for-at-least-two-months-with-ankle-injury |publisher=Sky Sports |date=2 February 2017 |accessdate=28 December 2017}}</ref> This ruled him out of the [[2017 EFL Cup Final]], which Southampton lost to [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] at [[Wembley Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title=Manchester United 3\u20132 Southampton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39018813 |website=BBC Sport |date=26 February 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nAfter a successful [[2016\u201317 Southampton F.C. season|2016\u201317 season]] at Southampton, Van Dijk was subject to interest from [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], who apologised to Southampton for an illegal approach for the player after having reportedly made clear his interest in a move to Liverpool.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40194862 |title=Virgil van Dijk: Liverpool apologise & end interest in Southampton defender |website=BBC Sport |date=7 June 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40164572 |title=Virgil van Dijk: Southampton defender keen on Liverpool move |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=5 June 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40170351 |title=Virgin van Dijk: Southampton to report Liverpool over approach |website=BBC Sport |date=6 June 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> On 7 August 2017, Van Dijk handed in a transfer request to Southampton and released a statement along with it, emphasising his wish to join a different club in the transfer window.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40855579 |title=Virgil van Dijk: Southampton defender hands in transfer request |website=BBC Sport |date=7 August 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==== 2017\u201318 season ====\nVan Dijk remained with Southampton for the start of the [[2017\u201318 Southampton F.C. season|2017\u201318 season]] and made his first appearance since being injured in January, coming on as a late substitute in a 1\u20130 victory at [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] on 26 September.<ref>{{cite news |first=Luke |last=Reddy |title=Crystal Palace 1\u20130 Southampton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41210053 |website=BBC Sport |date=16 September 2017 |accessdate=25 September 2017}}</ref> He made what turned out to be his final appearance for Southampton on 13 December 2017, in a 4\u20131 home defeat to Leicester.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42247116 |title=Southampton 1\u20134 Leicester City |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=13 December 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> It was also his last appearance in any of Southampton's matchday squads, as he was omitted from the squad for the rest of his tenure at the club in light of speculation surrounding his future.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/transfers/virgil-van-dijk-transfer-news-manchester-city-liverpool-left-out-of-squad-60m-latest-updates-a8128666.html |title=Virgil van Dijk left out of Southampton squad as Mauricio Pellegrino refuses to draw on Manchester City interest |first=Jack |last=De Menezes |newspaper=The Independent |location=London |date=26 December 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Liverpool===\nOn 27 December 2017, it was announced that Van Dijk would join Liverpool when the winter transfer window opened on 1 January 2018<ref name=pressLiverpool>{{cite web |title=Liverpool agree deal to sign Virgil van Dijk |url=http://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/285500-liverpool-agree-deal-to-sign-virgil-van-dijk |publisher=Liverpool F.C. |date=27 December 2017 |accessdate=28 December 2017}}</ref><ref name=southamptonpress>{{cite web |url=https://southamptonfc.com/news/2017-12-27/virgil-van-dijk-southampton-liverpool-transfer-agreement-announcement |title=Van Dijk deal agreed |publisher=Southampton F.C. |date=27 December 2017 |accessdate=28 December 2017}}</ref> for a reported fee of \u00a375&nbsp;million.<ref name=BBCLiverpool>{{cite news |title=Virgil van Dijk: Liverpool to sign Southampton defender for world record \u00a375m |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42496637 |website=BBC Sport |date=27 December 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> Former club Celtic would receive 10% of Van Dijk's transfer fee, due to a sell-on clause placed in his Southampton contract.<ref name=BBCLiverpool/><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11787/10906958/virgil-van-dijk-transfer-would-land-celtic-bumper-windfall |title=Virgil van Dijk transfer would land Celtic bumper windfall |first=Peter |last=Gilbert |publisher=Sky Sports |date=8 June 2017 |accessdate=28 December 2017}}</ref> Southampton claimed the undisclosed transfer fee would constitute a world record fee in football for a defender.<ref name=southamptonpress/>\n\n==== 2017\u201318 season ====\nHe made his debut for Liverpool on 5 January in the third round of the [[FA Cup]] and scored the winning goal with a late header in a 2\u20131 victory against local rivals [[Everton F.C.|Everton]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title=Liverpool 2\u20131 Everton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42508636 |website=BBC Sport |date=5 January 2018 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> In doing so, he became the first player since [[Bill White (footballer, born 1877)|Bill White]] in 1901 to score on his debut in the [[Merseyside derby]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/how-virgil-van-dijk-keeps-14120970 |title=How Virgil van Dijk keeps on creating Liverpool history \u2013 and the remarkable numbers behind derby triumph |work=Liverpool Echo |last=Doyle |first=Ian |date=6 January 2018 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> Van Dijk and [[Dejan Lovren]] built a strong partnership at the heart of Liverpool's defence, with the Dutchman being credited for improving Liverpool's previous defensive issues.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-champions-final-vandijk/van-dijk-has-made-me-a-better-player-says-liverpools-lovren-idUKKCN1IN301 |title=Van Dijk has made me a better player, says Liverpool's Lovren |last=Robinson |first=Neil |agency=Reuters |date=22 May 2018 |accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/apr/09/virgil-van-dijk-brings-calm-and-confidence-to-liverpool |title=Virgil van Dijk brings calm and collective spirit to Liverpool's defence |last=Hunter |first=Andy |date=9 April 2018 |work=The Guardian |accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/how-virgil-van-dijk-redefined-12213864 |title=How dominant Virgil van Dijk has redefined Liverpool's defence |last=Maddock |first=David |date=19 March 2018 |work=Daily Mirror |accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nVan Dijk was included in the [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League#Squad of the Season|UEFA Champions League Squad of the Season]], despite playing just half of the season in the [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]], with the ''UEFA Technical Observers'' saying: \"Van Dijk arrived at [[Anfield]] and provided composure and stability in the [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|competition's knockout stages]].\" Van Dijk played the full 90 minutes in the [[2018 UEFA Champions League Final]] against [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]], which Liverpool lost 1\u20133.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2018/matches/round=2000885/match=2021711/index.html |title=UEFA Champions League \u2013 Real Madrid-Liverpool |publisher=UEFA |accessdate=6 July 2018}}</ref> Van Dijk played 22 games in all competitions in his first season with the club, scoring 1 goal.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://us.soccerway.com/players/virgil-van-dijk/188624/ |title=Netherlands \u2013 V. van Dijk \u2013 Profile |website=soccerway |accessdate=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==== 2018\u201319 season ====\nOn 20 August 2018, Van Dijk was voted [[Player of the match|Man of the Match]] by [[BBC Sport]] and [[Sky Sports]] for his performance in a 2\u20130 win over [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45165666 |title=Crystal Palace 0\u20132 Liverpool: James Milner and Sadio Mane score as Reds move to six points |date=20 August 2018 |website=BBC Sport |accessdate=22 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/c-palace-vs-liverpool/390771 |title=Crystal Palace 0\u20132 Liverpool: James Milner and Sadio Mane see off 10-man Eagles |publisher=Sky Sports |accessdate=22 September 2018}}</ref> Van Dijk received the [[2018\u201319 Liverpool F.C. season#Liverpool Standard Chartered Player of the Month award|Liverpool Standard Chartered Player of the Month]] award for his performances in August.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/316051-virgil-van-dijk-standard-chartered-player-of-the-month |title=Virgil van Dijk named Standard Chartered Player of the Month |publisher=Liverpool F.C. |accessdate=22 September 2018}}</ref> On 2 December, Van Dijk was awarded an assist for the winning goal in a [[Merseyside derby|derby]] match against city rivals Everton. Liverpool won 1\u20130 thanks to Divock Origi's 96th-minute goal, set up by a Van Dijk volley and a subsequent error from Everton goalkeeper [[Jordan Pickford]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/blog/the-toe-poke/65/post/3716494/liverpools-virgil-van-dijk-gets-assist-vs-everton-despite-ball-hitting-crossbar-twice |title=Van Dijk gets 'assist' despite ball hitting crossbar TWICE |date=3 December 2018 |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=21 December 2018}}</ref> The Dutchman was ultimately awarded the [[Professional Footballers' Association|PFA]] Player of the Month for November 2018.<ref name=\"LFCPFA\">{{cite web |url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/327733-virgil-van-dijk-pfa-player-of-the-month |title=Van Dijk wins PFA Player of the Month award |author=Carroll, James |publisher=Liverpool F.C. |date=3 December 2018 |accessdate=21 December 2018}}</ref> On 21 December, Van Dijk scored his first goal in the Premier League for Liverpool in a 2\u20130 away win against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref name=\"Guardian\">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/dec/21/wolves-liverpool-premier-league-match-report |title=Liverpool's Mohamed Salah and Virgil van Dijk put Wolves in their place |last=James |first=Stuart |work=The Guardian |date=21 December 2018 |accessdate=22 December 2018}}</ref> The Dutchman continued his impressive form in the 2018\u201319 season by winning the Premier League Player of the Month prize for December 2018.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Matchett |first1=Karl |title=Liverpool scoop double Manager and Player of the Month awards for December |url=https://www.thisisanfield.com/2019/01/liverpool-scoop-double-manager-and-player-of-the-month-awards-for-impressive-december-form/ |website=thisisanfield.com |publisher=Soccer Publishing Limited|accessdate=20 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 February 2019, Van Dijk scored twice in a 5&ndash;0 win against [[Watford F.C.|Watford]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/liverpool-vs-watford/391033 |title=Liverpool 5-0 Watford |work=Sky Sports |accessdate=28 February 2019}}</ref> The following month, he scored once - his first goal in the Champions League for the club - and assisted another in a 3\u20131 win over [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]]. In doing so, he became the first player since [[Craig Bellamy]] in 2007 to score and assist a goal for Liverpool in a knock-out stage match away from home in the competition.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.caughtoffside.com/2019/03/13/liverpools-van-dijk-matches-bellamy-vs-barcelona-stat/|title=Virgil van Dijk does something no Liverpool player has managed for 12 years|publisher=CaughtOffside|last=Brus|first=Mark|date=14 March 2019|accessdate=14 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 April, he was one of six players nominated for the [[PFA Players' Player of the Year]] award alongside teammate [[Sadio Man\u00e9]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2019/04/20/pfa-player-yearvirgil-van-dijk-raheem-sterling-lead-way-six/|title=PFA Player of the Year: Virgil van Dijk and Raheem Sterling lead the way in six-man shortlist|publisher=The Telegraph|date=20 April 2019|accessdate=20 April 2019}}</ref> Four days later, he was named in the [[PFA Team of the Year]] alongside Liverpool teammates, [[Trent Alexander-Arnold]], Man\u00e9 and [[Andrew Robertson]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thepfa.com/news/2019/4/25/premier-league-team-of-the-year|title=PFA Premier League Team of the Year|publisher=The Player's Football Association|date=25 April 2019|accessdate=25 April 2019}}</ref> On 28 April 2019, he was named the [[PFA Players' Player of the Year|PFA Player of the Year]].<ref name=\"BBC 280419\">{{cite web |title=Virgil van Dijk and Vivianne Miedema win PFA player of the year awards |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48065752 |website=BBC Sport |accessdate=29 April 2019 |date=28 April 2019}}</ref> Following Liverpool's 2\u20130 victory over [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham]] in the [[2019 UEFA Champions League Final]] on 1 June, Van Dijk was named [[UEFA]]'s ''Man of the match''.<ref name=\"MOTM\">{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2019/matches/round=2000984/match=2025486/postmatch/report/ |title=Liverpool beat Tottenham to win sixth European Cup |website=UEFA.com |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |date=1 June 2019 |access-date=1 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== 2019\u201320 season ====\n[[File:Liverpool vs. Chelsea, UEFA Super Cup 2019-08-14 33 (cropped).jpg|200px|thumb|Van Dijk playing for Liverpool against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]]]\nIn August 2019, Van Dijk won UEFA player of the year award. On 2 September 2019, he was shortlisted in the final three of the best FIFA football awards.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.stroudnewsandjournal.co.uk/sport/national/17875102.van-dijk-take-messi-ronaldo-fifa-player-year/|title=Van Dijk to take on Messi and Ronaldo again for FIFA player of the year| date= 2 September 2019| accessdate=2 September 2019|work=Stroud News}}</ref> On 23 September 2019, he was voted runner up in [[The Best FIFA Men's Player]] and into the FIFA [[The_Best_FIFA_Football_Awards_2019#FIFA_FIFPro_Men's_World11|FIFpro Men's World 11]].<ref name= FIFA2019result>{{cite_web|url=https://img.fifa.com/image/upload/itqmjfv2sfevdiib4psc.pdf|title=Final Ranking the best FIFA Football awards|access-date=24 September 2019|publisher=FIFA}}</ref><ref name=FIFA2019vote>{{cite_web|url=https://img.fifa.com/image/upload/z0gygcuwnxuz6pimfuhm.pdf|title=Voting breakdown in the best Fifa Men's player 2019|access-date=24 September 2019|publisher=FIFA}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.stroudnewsandjournal.co.uk/sport/national/17922187.rapinoe-calls-change-wins-big-alongside-messi-klopp/|title=Rapinoe calls for change as she wins big alongside Messi and Klopp| date=23 September 2019| accessdate=23 September 2019|work=Stroud News}}</ref> In October 2019, Van Dijk was shortlisted as one in 30 football players for the [[Ballon d'Or]].<ref>{{cite_web|first=Brendan|last= Hodrien|url=https://www.rousingthekop.com/2019/10/22/seven-liverpool-players-up-for-ballon-dor-as-reds-dominate-the-shortlist/|title=Seven Liverpool players up for Ballon d'Or as Reds dominate the shortlist|date=22 October 2019| accessdate=22 October 2019|website=Rousing The Kop}}</ref> At the event in December, he finished runner-up behind [[Lionel Messi]].<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.manisteenews.com/sports/article/US-soccer-star-Rapinoe-wins-Ballon-d-Or-14876298.php|title=Megan Rapinoe, Lionel Messi win Ballon d\u2019Or awards|accessdate=2 December 2019|website=News Manistee Advocate|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203150930/https://www.manisteenews.com/sports/article/US-soccer-star-Rapinoe-wins-Ballon-d-Or-14876298.php|archive-date=3 December 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 21 December 2019, after missing the semi-final of the [[2019 FIFA Club World Cup]] with illness, Van Dijk played in the [[2019 FIFA Club World Cup Final|final]] against [[Clube de Regatas do Flamengo|Flamengo]] with Liverpool winning the trophy for the first time in the club\u2019s history.<ref name=\"FIFA Final\">{{cite news |url=https://www.fifa.com/clubworldcup/news/firmino-writes-liverpool-into-club-world-cup-history |title=Firmino writes Liverpool into Club World Cup history |website=FIFA.com |publisher=F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Football Association |date=21 December 2019 |access-date=21 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Harry|last=Poole|title=Firmino winner seals Club World Cup win |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50869633|accessdate=22 December 2019 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> \n\nVan Dijk received further recognition following the turn of the year, when he was named in the 2019 [[UEFA Team of the Year]].<ref name=UTOTY2019>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2637433.html|title=UEFA.com fans' Team of the Year 2019 revealed|publisher=UEFA|date=15 January 2020|accessdate=15 January 2020}}</ref> On 19 January 2020, Van Dijk scored his first [[Liverpool F.C.\u2013Manchester United F.C. rivalry|North-West Derby]] goal against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in Liverpool\u2019s 2\u20130 win at Anfield in the Premier League.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2020/01/19/liverpool-vs-manchester-united-premier-league-live-score-latest/|title=Liverpool brush Manchester United aside in breathless contest to go 16 points clear at the top of the table|last=Burt|first=Jason|date=19 January 2020|work=The Telegraph|access-date=20 January 2020|last2=Tweedale|first2=Alistair|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51080695|title=Liverpool 2-0 Manchester United: Virgil van Dijk and Mo Salah goals secure win |publisher=BBC Sport |date=19 January 2020 |access-date=20 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nVan Dijk made his full international debut for [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] on 10 October 2015, in a 2\u20131 victory away from home against [[Kazakhstan national football team|Kazakhstan]] in a [[UEFA Euro 2016]] qualifier.<ref>{{cite web |title=Successful Saturday for Saints stars |url=https://southamptonfc.com/news/2015-10-10/successful-saturday-for-saints-stars |publisher=Southampton F.C. |date=10 October 2015 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe was awarded the [[captain (association football)|captain]]cy of his country by manager [[Ronald Koeman]] on 22 March 2018,<ref>{{cite web|title=Van Dijk named new Netherlands captain |first=Daniel |last=Karell |date=22 March 2018 |accessdate=22 March 2018 |publisher=NBC Sports |url=http://soccer.nbcsports.com/2018/03/22/van-dijk-named-new-netherlands-captain/}}</ref> and his first match as captain was a 1\u20130 home friendly defeat by [[England national football team|England]] the next day.<ref>{{cite web|title=Netherlands 0\u20131 England |first=Phil |last=McNulty |date=23 March 2018 |accessdate=24 March 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/43380175}}</ref> On 26 March, he scored his first international goal to conclude a 3\u20130 win over European champions [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] at the [[Stade de Gen\u00e8ve]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Soccer \u2013 Portugal suffer first-half collapse in 3\u20130 loss to Dutch |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-friendly-por-ned/soccer-portugal-suffer-first-half-collapse-in-3-0-loss-to-dutch-idUKKBN1H22S7 |accessdate=26 March 2018 |agency=Reuters |date=26 March 2018}}</ref> On 13 October, he scored in a 3\u20130 win over [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014 World Cup]] champions [[Germany national football team|Germany]] in the [[2018\u201319 UEFA Nations League|UEFA Nations League]].<ref>{{Cite web  |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45851123 |title=Netherlands 3\u20130 Germany: Liverpool's Virgil van Dijk and Georginio Wijnaldum score for hosts |date=13 October 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=13 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nVan Dijk is a physically strong, right-footed [[centre-back]], who usually features on the left-hand side of central defence, although he can also play as a right-sided centre-back.<ref name=\"Best Defender-sportbible\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.sportbible.com/football/reactions-take-a-bow-news-virgil-van-dijk-voted-the-best-defender-in-world-football-20190316|title=Virgil Van Dijk Voted The Best Defender In World Football|date=16 March 2019|website=www.sportbible.com|access-date=20 April 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"best defender-sky\"/><ref name=NMcG>{{cite web|title=Virgil van Dijk 'can be a great' as Liverpool agree to pay \u00a375m for defender |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40730793 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 December 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref> He is gifted with pace,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/1004040/watch-virgil-van-dijk-burns-premier-league-faster-player-in-a-sprint-liverpool-wolves/ |title=Watch: Virgil van Dijk burns \u2018Premier League\u2019s faster player\u2019 in a sprint |publisher=Fox Sports Asia |last1=Rangarajan |first1=Aditya |date=22 December 2018 |accessdate=3 June 2019 }}</ref> good technique, and an eye for goal, and is an effective [[Direct free kick|set-piece taker]]. Regarding his ability, former Celtic teammate [[Kris Commons]] commented that Van Dijk was \"comfortable on the ball\", also noting that \"He had good technique and a wonderful right foot. He was good on set-pieces, some of the free-kicks he scored for Celtic are absolute wonders. He could read the game well. He had an aura about him, a confidence, because I think he knew he was good.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/story-telling/15117/11684250/how-virgil-van-dijk-became-the-premier-leagues-top-defender |title=How Virgil van Dijk became the best |publisher=Sky Sports |last1=Bate |first1=Adam |accessdate=3 June 2019 }}</ref>\n\nNeil McGuinness, senior scout at Celtic when Van Dijk was signed, called him \"everything you would want if you could create a profile of the ideal central defender\", praising him as a \"very smooth ball-playing defender\" who possesses aerial prowess, skills from dead ball situations, and \"strong leadership qualities\", while commenting that since his move to England, he is \"more tactically aware now [...] his anticipation and timing has improved and he is a lot more of an all-rounder\".<ref name=NMcG/> McGuinness believes Van Dijk's \"biggest problem\" is that he \"can switch off when the game is comfortable\".<ref name=NMcG/>\n\nIn a 2019 interview with ''[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]'', when [[Lionel Messi]] was asked why Van Dijk was so difficult to beat, the Argentine responded: \"He is a defender who knows how to judge his timing and wait for the right moment to challenge or jockey [the attacker]. He is very fast and big, but he has a lot of agility for his height. He is fast because of its [sic] great stride, and he is impressive both in defence and attack because he scores lots of goals.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/barcelona/2019/10/17/5da81c0122601d1b308b458c.html |title=Messi: The body rules and I have to take more care of myself than before |website=www.Marca.com|last1=Gallardo |first1=Juan Ignacio |last2=Rojo |first2=Luis F. |date=17 October 2019 |accessdate=17 October 2019 }}</ref> That same year, [[Paul Merson]] described Van Dijk as \"the best in the world, and I think by a long way, as a defensive centre-half.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11669/11659594/virgil-van-dijk-the-best-defender-in-the-world-says-paul-merson |title=Virgil van Dijk the best defender in the world, says Paul Merson |publisher=Sky Sports |last1=Merson |first1=Paul |date=9 March 2019 |accessdate=8 April 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==Sponsorship==\nVan Dijk features as the cover star of the champions edition of [[EA Sports]]' [[FIFA (video game series)|''FIFA'']] video game ''[[FIFA 20]]''.<ref>{{cite news |title=Virgil van Dijk to be EA SPORTS' FIFA 20 Champions Edition cover star |url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/announcements/357944-virgil-van-dijk-fifa-20-champions-edition-cover-star |accessdate=26 July 2019 |work=LiverpoolFC.com}}</ref> He is endorsed by sportswear company [[Nike football|Nike]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/Companies/bmR0I1uUxIr0zZjXAlEAII/Nike-gains-a-step-on-Adidas-in-competition-for-top-football.html|title=Nike gains a step on Adidas in competition for top football stars|last=Weiss|first=Richard|date=2018-01-26|website=www.livemint.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-05}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nVan Dijk commonly uses only his first name on the kit. According to his uncle Steven, this is because of a feud with his father.<ref>{{cite web |title=Here Is Why Virgil van Dijk Only Uses His First Name On Kit |url=https://www.footyheadlines.com/2019/03/here-is-why-virgil-van-dijk-only-uses-first-name-on-kit.html |website=Footy Headlines |accessdate=18 March 2019 |date=18 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 11 March 2020}}\n\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|National Cup{{efn|Includes [[KNVB Cup]], [[Scottish Cup]], [[FA Cup]]}}\n!colspan=2|League Cup{{efn|Includes [[Scottish League Cup]], [[EFL Cup|League Cup/EFL Cup]]}}\n!colspan=2|Europe\n!colspan=2|Other\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[FC Groningen|Groningen]]\n|[[2010\u201311 Eredivisie|2010\u201311]]<ref name=Soccerway/>\n|[[Eredivisie]]\n|5||2||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||5||2\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Eredivisie|2011\u201312]]<ref name=Soccerway/>\n|Eredivisie\n|23||3||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||24||3\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Eredivisie|2012\u201313]]<ref name=Soccerway>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/virgil-van-dijk/188624/ |title=V. Van Dijk: Summary |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=21 December 2018}}</ref>\n|Eredivisie\n|34||2||3||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||37||2\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!62||7||4||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||66||7\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]\n|[[2013\u201314 Celtic F.C. season|2013\u201314]]<ref name=sb1314>{{soccerbase season|59442|2013|accessdate=29 September 2016}}</ref>\n|[[Scottish Premiership]]\n|36||5||2||0||1||0||8{{efn|name=UCL|Appearances in [[UEFA Champions League]]}}||0||colspan=2|\u2014||47||5\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 Celtic F.C. season|2014\u201315]]<ref name=sb1415>{{soccerbase season|59442|2014|accessdate=29 September 2016}}</ref>\n|Scottish Premiership\n|35||4||5||4||4||0||14{{efn|Six appearances in UEFA Champions League; eight appearances in [[UEFA Europa League]]}}||2||colspan=2|\u2014||58||10\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 Celtic F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref name=sb1516/>\n|Scottish Premiership\n|5||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||5{{efn|name=UCL}}||0||colspan=2|\u2014||10||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!76||9||7||4||5||0||27||2||colspan=2|\u2014||115||15\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]]\n|[[2015\u201316 Southampton F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref name=sb1516>{{soccerbase season|59442|2015|accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n|[[Premier League]]\n|34||3||1||0||3||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||38||3\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Southampton F.C. season|2016\u201317]]<ref name=sb1617>{{soccerbase season|59442|2016|accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|21||1||1||1||2||0||6{{efn|Appearances in UEFA Europa League}}||2||colspan=2|\u2014||30||4\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 Southampton F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=sb1718/>\n|Premier League\n|12||0||colspan=2|\u2014||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||12||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!67||4||2||1||5||0||6||2||colspan=2|\u2014||80||7\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]\n|[[2017\u201318 Liverpool F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=sb1718>{{soccerbase season|59442|2017|accessdate=12 August 2018}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|14||0||2||1||colspan=2|\u2014||6{{efn|name=UCL}}||0||colspan=2|\u2014||22||1\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 Liverpool F.C. season|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{soccerbase season|59442|2018|accessdate=10 August 2019}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|38||4||0||0||0||0||12{{efn|name=UCL}}||2||colspan=2|\u2014||50||6\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 Liverpool F.C. season|2019\u201320]]<ref>{{soccerbase season|59442|2019|accessdate=19 January 2020}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|29||4||1||0||0||0||8{{efn|name=UCL}}||0||3{{efn|One appearance in [[FA Community Shield]], one appearance in [[UEFA Super Cup]], one appearance in [[FIFA Club World Cup]]|name=|group=}}||0||41||4\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!81||8||3||1||0||0||26||2||3||0||113||11\n|-\n!colspan=3|Career total\n!286||28||16||6||10||0||59||6||3||0||374||40\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\n===International===\n{{updated|match played 16 November 2019}}<ref name=NFT>{{NFT player |id=60815 |name=Van Dijk, Virgil |accessdate=10 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|+ Appearances and goals by national team and year\n|-\n\n!National team!!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=5|[[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]]\n|2015||3||0\n|-\n|2016||9||0\n|-\n|2017||4||0\n|-\n|2018||8||3\n|-\n|2019||9||1\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total||33||4\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n: ''As of match played on 9 September 2019. Netherlands score listed first, score column indicates score after each Van Dijk goal.''<ref name=NFT/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ International goals by date, venue, cap, opponent, score, result and competition\n|-\n!scope=col|No.\n!scope=col|Date\n!scope=col|Venue\n!scope=col|Cap\n!scope=col|Opponent\n!scope=col|Score\n!scope=col|Result\n!scope=col|Competition\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|1\n|26 March 2018||[[Stade de Gen\u00e8ve]], Geneva, Switzerland||align=center|18||{{fb|POR}}||align=center|3\u20130||align=center|3\u20130||[[Exhibition game#Association football|Friendly]]\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|2\n|13 October 2018||[[Johan Cruyff Arena]], Amsterdam, Netherlands||align=center|22||rowspan=2|{{fb|GER}}||align=center|1\u20130||align=center|3\u20130||rowspan=2|[[2018\u201319 UEFA Nations League A]]\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|3\n|19 November 2018||[[Arena AufSchalke]], Gelsenkirchen, Germany||align=center|24||align=center|2\u20132||align=center|2\u20132\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|4\n|21 March 2019||[[De Kuip]], Rotterdam, Netherlands||align=center|25||{{fb|BLR}}||align=center|4\u20130||align=center|4\u20130||[[UEFA Euro 2020 qualification]]\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Celtic'''\n*[[Scottish Premiership]]: [[2013\u201314 Scottish Premiership|2013\u201314]], [[2014\u201315 Scottish Premiership|2014\u201315]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/virgil-van-dijk_prs276965/person.shtml |title=Virgil van Dijk |publisher=Eurosport |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Scottish League Cup]]: [[2014\u201315 Scottish League Cup|2014\u201315]]<ref name=2015SLC/>\n\n'''Liverpool'''\n*[[UEFA Champions League]]: [[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League|2018\u201319]];<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48368443 |title=Tottenham Hotspur 0\u20132 Liverpool |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=1 June 2019 |accessdate=1 June 2019}}</ref> runner-up: [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League|2017\u201318]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44258022 |title=Real Madrid 3\u20131 Liverpool |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=26 May 2018 |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA Super Cup]]: [[2019 UEFA Super Cup|2019]]<ref>{{