nounced that their SimulDubs would be delayed for the rest of the Winter season as well as the upcoming seasons, but they stated that simulcasts in English subtitles will continue as scheduled. But on, April 11, 2020; Funimation announced that their simuldubs have slowly resumed production but on a work from home basis.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.funimation.com/blog/2020/03/18/simuldub-delays-anime-winter-spring-2020-funimation-simulcasts-on-track/ |title=Update: Spring 2020 Simulcasts On-Track; SimulDub Delays |website=funimation.com| |access-date=March 18, 2020}}</ref><ref>https://www.funimation.com/blog/2020/04/10/my-hero-academia-simuldub-returns-from-home/</ref> On March 27, 2020, [[Crunchyroll]] announced that they will also be delaying English Dub productions of their licensed anime series as a result of the pandemic.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2020/03/27-1/an-update-to-our-english-dubs |title=An Update to Our English Dubs |website=crunchyroll.com| |access-date=March 27, 2020}}</ref> On April 2, 2020, [[Sentai Filmworks|Sentai Filmworks' HIDIVE]] announced that they will also be delaying dubbed titles until further notice.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-04-02/hidive-postpones-future-streaming-dubcasts/.158182|title=HIDIVE Postpones Future Streaming Dubcasts|website=Anime News Network|language=en|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref> In early April 2020, many anime series were revealed to be postponed from their intended broadcast dates due to Japan declaring a state of emergency on April 6, 2020 because of the increase of [[COVID-19]] cases in the nation.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/07/world/asia/japan-coronavirus-emergency.html |title= Japan Declared a Coronavirus Emergency. Is It Too Late? |website=nytimes.com| |access-date=April 7, 2020}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+\n!Name\n!Animation Studio\n!Network\n!Reason\n!Source\n|-\n|[[A3!|''A3! Season Autumn & Winte